title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Place in a preheated oven set at 300° and cook for 40 minutes or until done.

title: shoney's cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add cocoa and eggs, then flour and remaining ingredients in alternation.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: versatile schaum torte
directions: Beat egg whites in large bowl until very stiff, about 4 minutes.
Turn to medium speed.
Add sugar, gradually.
Then add salt, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy, about 5 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and pour over white layer.
Refrigerate.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip (thawed) with the yogurt and pour into graham crust. Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Garnish, if desired.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add soup and cheeses.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli, almonds, garlic powder, Worcestershire and pepper sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes. Serve in large round rye bread that has been hollowed out.
Use bread pieces for dipping.
You will need an extra loaf of rye bread.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Tear ham into pan; heat and add remaining ingredients. Simmer.

title: dilly dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight for flavors to blend.
Serve with any raw vegetable such as broccoli, cauliflower, celery, carrots or squash.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the strawberries and Cool Whip with hands and put into shell.
Cool until ready to use.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 10 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate in large pan.
Cook to soft ball stage (230°).
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Put into refrigerator to cool.
When firm, cover both sides lightly with melted chocolate.

title: lincoln cheese log
directions: Blend all ingredients except dried beef.
Form into ball or log.
Roll in dried beef mixture.
Age at least 2 days.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Chop stewed tomatoes; add with liquid to meat.
Add undrained kidney beans, tomato sauce, water and seasoning mix.
Simmer, covered, for at least 30 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag; add to vinegar mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and milk.
Tear up cake and pour cream cheese mixture over cake.
Mix glaze and strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: emogene's chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done. Cut up chicken in small pieces.
Melt margarine in baking dish. Put chicken in baking dish. Pour soup over chicken.
Mix stuffing with broth from cooking the chicken.
Spread on top of chicken.
Pour milk over stuffing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, reserve 1/2 of the tomato sauce.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Pour remaining sauce over loaves.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.

Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate morsels until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with walnut halves and press into fudge.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: red, white, and green jello
directions: Wet 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, then grease with mayonnaise for easier serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with lemon juice.
Add shrimp and green onions to cream cheese mixture.
Add enough mayonnaise to give a consistency for dipping potato chips or crackers.
Season with hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar, bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello and cream cheese.
Stir and let cool.
When cool, fold into apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour into baking dish and chill until firm.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Thaw vegetables and drain.
Add soup, cream, pepper and pimientos.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook shells; drain on paper towel.
Combine cheeses, egg, salt, oregano and pepper.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Place in dish; cover with sauce.
Sprinkle some Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: small cheesecakes
directions: Place wafers, flat side down, in cupcake papers.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spoon into cups.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and top with pie filling.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large skillet, crumble meat with onion and garlic.
Break up pieces of meat with fork and cook until it loses its red color. Drain off excess fat.
In slow cooking pot, combine browned meat, onion and garlic with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over hot spaghetti.
May be frozen.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and pull apart. Combine sour cream and chicken soup; heat. Place chicken in casserole dish. Pour soup and sour cream over chicken. Crumble crackers over casserole. Melt butter; pour over crackers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onions. Pour into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, crumbs and almonds; sprinkle over vegetables. Bake uncovered.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
May add 1 cup pecans if desired.

title: fresh basil and tomato pesto without pine nuts(from your garden)
directions: Food process the basil, olive oil and Parmesan cheese about 45 seconds and remove.
Add tomatoes.
Mix together with basil mixture.
Pour over vermicelli cooked al dente.

title: strawberry pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Beat ingredients until resembles coarse crumbs; press firmly and evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer slowly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raspberry jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and mix with other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar and Karo syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole (glass) dish.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and cook 3 1/2 minutes more on High.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Stir well. Cook on High for 1 minute.
Add baking soda and mix well until foamy.
Quickly pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and then break and eat.

title: bran bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Add to sifted flour and mix well.
Add All-Bran.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Brush top with melted butter.
Punch down and let rise again.
Roll dough for 3 (5 x 9-inch) pans and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwaved apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, lemon peel and cinnamon.
Toss with apples and lemon juice.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut vents into crust.
Microwave at High 10 to 12 minutes or until filling is bubbly.
Then bake in conventional oven at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: eggroll sauce
directions: Cook until mixture thickens.

title: shepherd pie
directions: In saucepan, cook celery, onions and thyme in butter until vegetables are tender.
Add soup, water, beef and heat.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole, spoon potatoes in mounds around the edge. Broil until potatoes are brown.

title: 2-step beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef. (When browning beef, add onion.) Add soup, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and milk. Then stir in mushrooms. Serve over noodles.

title: egg and bacon casserole
directions: Put the cheese in the white sauce and stir.
Butter a large casserole dish; layer the eggs and bacon.
Pour a little sauce between layers.
Pour the remaining sauce over the eggs and bacon. Sprinkle the crumbled potato chips over the top.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.
Makes a very good breakfast or brunch dish.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Crush Doritos in bag. Place half on bottom of an oiled dish (3-quart flat). Brown ground beef, seasoned with salt, pepper and dash of garlic powder. Drain and place over Doritos. Pour the hot chili beans over meat. Layer chopped onion over beans, then slice thin layer Velveeta cheese on top of onions. Then layer with rest of Doritos. Mix
cream of chicken soup with Ro-Tel tomatoes (mashed) and top with this mixture. Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini
directions: Salt and pepper zucchini; dip in flour.
Saute in hot oil.
Put in baking dish and set aside.
Saute onions until nicely brown. Stir in sugar and wine well.
Swizzle over zucchini.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel dip
directions: Melt ingredients together slowly.
Quarter apples and brush with lemon juice to keep white, then dip.

title: natural gas broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix together onion, soup, eggs and mayo.
Stir and drain broccoli.
Pour into greased, oblong pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine crumbs with melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix onions, mayonnaise, cheddar and Tabasco.
Spread into a small baking dish.
Top with Parmesan and sprinkle with paprika to taste.
Bake in preheated oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: cooked finger paint
directions: Mix flour and water.
Stir until smooth. Bring to a boil, still stirring.
Cook until it is thick as pudding.
Then cool and add dishwashing liquid until thin enough for finger painting.
Add a few drops of food coloring.

title: peanut butter and jelly thumbprints
directions: Cream together the shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg. Add dry ingredients; stir well.
Shape into little balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Place on ungreased pan, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 7 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.
Serve with fruit of your choice.

title: cucumber sandwich filling
directions: Grate peeled cucumber, sprinkle with salt, and allow to drain for 30 minutes.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
Best when spread on Swedish rye bread.

title: green chilies and cheese
directions: Place chilies in a 9-inch round pie dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Club crackers.

title: company best pickles
directions: Place whole cucumbers in a glass or stoneware jar.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand overnight. Drain.
Repeat 3 days.
On the fifth day, drain and slice cucumber in 1/2-inch pieces. Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers. Let stand 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Yields 7 pints.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place soup meat, onion, salt, pepper and water into pressure cooker. Cover and cook 50 minutes after control jiggles. Reduce pressure normally for 5 minutes. Then place pan under water. Strain the broth into a large pan. Separate meat from fat. Add meat to broth, leaving meat in small pieces. Cut up, season and partially cook potatoes and carrots (separately). Drain. Season and drain all other vegetables. Add vegetables to beef and broth. Bring to a boil and cook fast 5 to 10 minutes. Then simmer for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar. Bring milk to boil and add to dry ingredients, stirring constantly. Cook this in a double boiler, stirring until thick, about 15 minutes. Add egg yolks and butter; cook 2 minutes longer. Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue or Cool Whip (your preference).

title: fudge dream bars
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa over low heat.
Beat eggs well; sift in sugar and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour cocoa mixture into egg mixture; blend well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pour into large greased pan or 3 (8-inch) pans.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Shape and refrigerate. Circle with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: diet breakers baked chicken
directions: Wash and place chicken in a pan.
Pour water in pan.
Baste with margarine, sprinkle with garlic, salt, pepper and sunflower seeds.
Place cloves in the middle of chicken.
Cover chicken with bacon strips.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chill out chili
directions: Cook meat, onions and garlic in oil about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chili powder, cumin and oregano and salt over meat.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve topped with sour cream, chopped green onions and picante sauce.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat to boil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove and beat until thickened.
Pour in buttered pan. Let it set for 15 minutes and serve.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, stir soup until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Add stuffing mix, chicken, broccoli, celery and 1 cup of the cheese.
Spread mixture in greased baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes. Top with remaining cheese. Bake until cheese melts.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Beat in salt, sugar and flavoring.
Beat in milk which has been heated to boiling with the butter.
Add flour and baking powder which were sifted together. Pour very quickly into greased and floured pan (1 large layer pan).
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: skyline chili party dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch microwavable casserole dish.
Sprinkle cream cheese with diced onions.
Heat chili according to instruction on package and pour over onions and cream cheese.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.

title: crockery cocoa
directions: Combine milk,
cocoa
and
sugar in crock-pot.
Stir in vanilla and warm water.
Stir to dissolve.
Cook on low 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato paste, water, onion, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Simmer.
Cook the lasagne noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Mix together cottage cheese and eggs.
Spray pan with Pam.
Spread a small amount of meat sauce in bottom of pan.
Arrange ingredients in layers:
noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Do not put cottage cheese in top layer (you will have 3 layers).
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot at 375°.

title: peach apricot cobbler(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium saucepan, mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in 1/2 cup each of reserved peach and apricot juices.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add peaches and apricots.
Spoon fruit mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix all together and spread on a flour tortilla.
Cut with a pizza cutter in 1-inch lengths.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix in wet ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes with or without baking cups.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy lemonade
directions: Wash lemons thoroughly.
Slice lemons into large pan or bowl. Remove
seeds.
Add sugar.	Mash sugar and lemons well. Add water. Refrigerate.
After one hour, remove rinds.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and sour cream.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Thoroughly grease a 10-inch tube pan.

title: beef pocket sandwiches
directions: Brown meat and pour off excess fat.
Add parsley and seasonings.
Simmer.
Blend in milk, Miracle Whip and chopped tomato.
Stir over low heat until warm.
Spoon into rounds of pita bread.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes done first; put aside.
Melt butter in skillet. Add onion and pepper; saute.
Stir in flour, then milk and 3/4 of cheese.
Cook until thickened.
Makes a gravy.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of unsalted boiling water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Combine soup and next 6 ingredients; add broccoli, stirring well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Combine stuffing mix and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Melt butter in pan; mix persimmon mix, flour, milk, margarine and sugar together.
Beat eggs; put in last.
Bake at 350° or until brown.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: baked apple(snack)
directions: Dice apples.
Leave peel on.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples in microwave-safe bowl.
Top with butter. Bake in microwave 2 minutes on High setting.

title: saucy beef over rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onion and celery.
Combine all other ingredients in large pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 15 minutes.
Add water if needed.
Add meat mixture.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve on buns.
Garnish with dill pickles.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly and spoon off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 1/2 to 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: stir-n-roll pastry
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix flour and salt.
Measure oil and milk into 1 measuring cup, but don't stir.
Add all at once to flour; stir until mixed.
Press into a smooth ball.
Cut in halves and flatten slightly.

title: mom's chocolate cake
directions: Melt together the cocoa, shortening and hot water and let cool.
Add to sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs and add sour milk in which soda has been dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven.
Cook 40 minutes.

title: ham and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and empty into large pot.
Add chopped onion, bone and meat chunks.
Cover with water about 1-inch above beans and cook slowly. Simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Stir sparingly with wooden or plastic spoon.
May need to add water. When done, remove bone from pot.
Take remaining meat off bone. Cut up and add back.

title: potato-cheese casserole
directions: In very large bowl, mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bachelor's delight
directions: If your wife is not home (or if you don't have one), look in the refrigerator for leftovers.
Get out a big cast-iron skillet and throw the leftovers in it.
Crack some eggs (4 or 5 if you are hungry) and stir it all up together.
Fry on high.
(Throw the burned parts to the cat and dog.)
Pull out the eggshells as you eat.
One problem:
Kids don't like this very well.
Open a can of chili for them.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Put in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain fat.
Add to crock-pot along with remaining ingredients.
Stir together well.
Cook on low for 4 to 9 hours. Absolutely delicious!

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain excess grease. Add onion, bell pepper and tomato. Let simmer. Add salt and pepper to taste. Boil macaroni in salted water. Drain and add to meat mixture. Add a few cubes of Velveeta into mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle a layer of bread crumbs on bottom. Combine rest of ingredients and place on top of bread crumbs. Top with bits of butter and cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: In large bowl, beat two eggs and almond extract.
With large spoon gently stir in cherry pie filling.
Add cake mix and gently stir with spoon until just moistened.
Spoon into 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While warm frost with Chocolate Fudge Frosting.

title: taffy bars
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Boil 3 minutes (exactly).
Pour over graham crackers, using 2 cooking sheets.
Graham crackers should be close together.
Immediately sprinkle on chopped nuts.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out and immediately transfer bars to a spread out paper bag sprayed with Pam.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the stuffing mix.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Cover; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat yolks; add corn, flour and seasoning, butter and cream. Blend.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in corn mixture.
Drop onto hot greased griddle, from a tablespoon.
Cook until brown. Turn on other side; cook until brown.
Serves 6.

title: wine cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix 5 minutes.
Bake in angel food cake pan for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 25 minutes.
Invert, remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Add poppy seed if desired for cake.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin.	Mix crumbs with pecans and
pour condensed milk over them.
Add other ingredients, mixing well until all are moistened.
Then pack in dish, firmly, and put in refrigerator.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs. Add oleo, oil and the sugars.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Add lemon flavoring.
Form into balls.
Flatten with a glass.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, including fruit cocktail juice until well mixed.
Pour into 9-inch square greased baking dish. Sprinkle top with mixture of brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: colossal caramel apple trifle
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using 2 greased 9-inch round baking pans. Cool for 10 minutes before removing to wire racks to cool completely.

title: spiced fruit compote
directions: Drain peaches and pears; reserve 1 1/2 cups syrup.
In 4-quart saucepan, heat raisins, water, brown sugar, salt, cornstarch, spices and fruit syrup to boiling, stirring often.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add pears and peaches (heat thoroughly).
Serve warm.
Serve as an accompaniment to meat. This is good at Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: cheese crisp cookies
directions: Mix grated cheese and margarine.
Beat slowly.
Add flour; mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls and mash flat with a fork.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pink cow
directions: In a blender mix milk, strawberries and orange juice. Taste and add sugar as needed.

title: turkey breast in a bag
directions: You will need 1 large cooking bag (Reynolds brand).

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Mix
together
egg,
milk
and corn meal.
Fry meat and onion until
meat
has turned.
Add tomato sauce, vegetables, chili powder
and garlic.
Add a little water to make mixture thinner. Put
in
casserole
dish.
Pour corn meal mixture on top.
Add grated cheese on top of corn meal mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle grated cheese to cover bottom of unbaked pie crust. Drain vegetables that are already cooked and add mushrooms.
Add to pie crust.
In bowl whip eggs with wire whip.
Add milk and Cheddar cheese soup and whip until blended.
Pour over top of vegetables.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain liquid and remove bones from salmon. Mix together salmon, onion, egg, Old Bay seasoning and cracker crumbs.
Mold mixture into 8 patties.
Heat oil in skillet. Cook salmon patties on both sides until golden brown.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and freeze.
Set out before serving.

title: pumpkin pie(crustless)
directions: Mix all together with an electric beater.
Pour into a greased pie plate (large).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes with mixer; add all other ingredients.
Blend well.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with topping.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Reserve 3/4 cup of cake mix.
To the remaining mix, add oleo and egg.
Mix well.
Place in well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tasty sandwiches
directions: Mix all.
Spread on party rye bread.
Freeze until ready to use.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 60 sandwiches.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: Combine seasoned salt, onion powder, pepper and garlic powder; rub onto roast.
In a skillet, brown roast in oil.
Place in a roasting pan.
Add water, onion, green pepper and seasonings. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until roast is tender.
Remove and keep warm.
Discard bay leaf.
Skim fat from pan juices.
Measure juices and return to pan.
For each cup of juices, combine 1 tablespoon flour with 2 tablespoons water; mix well.
Stir flour mixture into pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Serve gravy with roast.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: rhubarb conserve
directions: Cut up oranges or grind skins.
Cut up rhubarb.
Mix sugar and fruit, let stand overnight.
Boil for 45 minutes, stir frequently. (One-quarter pound blanched, chopped almonds may be added, if desired.)
Seal in glass jars.

title: cape verdean baked bread
directions: *Recommend King Arthur or Santa Isabel pre-cooked Spanish cornflour.

title: hamburger steak and potatoes
directions: Shape hamburger, bread and milk into patties.
Brown in electric frypan.
Add potatoes, onion, soup and water.
Simmer until done.

title: do-ahead brunch casserole
directions: The night before serving, place hash browns on the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating.
Top hash browns with 1 cup of cheese and the strips of ham.
Beat together egg substitute, 2 1/4 cup of milk, mustard and pepper in a bowl.
Pour over ham.
Cover with foil and refrigerate until morning.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2 baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Mix soup and milk. Stir well. Spoon soup mixture over chicken breasts. Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle margarine over top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugared cranberries
directions: Mix egg white, water and sugar together.
Dip cranberries in egg white, then in sugar.
Let dry.
Keeps awhile.
Has surprise tart, sweet flavor.

title: beef lombardi
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain.
Stir in chopped tomatoes and next 4 ingredients; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and bay leaf.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: thelma lou's chocolate cream dessert
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate, stirring until smooth. Remove from heat and add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold into the chocolate mixture.
Spoon lightly into sherbet glasses.
Chill.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Spread 1/2 cup brown sugar in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and arrange apple slices on top.
Cover with lemon juice and set aside.
Cream 1/2 cup butter and remaining sugars until fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk.
Spread batter over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Place on cooling rack 10 minutes, then turn upside-down on plate and top with whipped cream.

title: peach pie
directions: Sprinkle peaches with lemon juice and sugar; let stand 1 hour. Drain.
Measure 1 cup of this syrup and add cornstarch.
Blend. Stir over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and extract.
Cool.

title: german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk over low heat, stirring until melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into chocolate mixture and blend until smooth.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze about 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: pasties
directions: Combine meat, potatoes (the proportions vary depending on taste and food budget, can be equal parts), onion, salt and pepper.
Roll pie dough into 6 x 6-inch squares.
Put about 1 cup mixture in center.
Top with a dab of butter.
Fold in sides, then roll up ends to form pockets.
Continue until all meat and potatoes are gone.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be served warm, opened up and topped with butter or the next day cold, spread with butter on the outside.

title: best ever salad dressing
directions: Beat in electric mixer and keep refrigerated.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: daddy frank's sweet potato casserole(great for holidays!)
directions: Mix all and put in a casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: If whole tomatoes, break up in saucepan or whatever pot you choose.
Add butter and sugar to tomatoes (I usually add sugar until I have sweetened to taste).
Bring to a boil and add dumplings.
Turn down heat, cover and simmer until dumplings are cooked.

title: seafood salad
directions: Grind
in
food
chopper
tuna	fish,
crabmeat,
eggs, pickles,
celery and onion.
Blend vinegar, mayonnaise, sugar, seasoning
salt and cream cheese together.	Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Garnish with stuffed olives.
(One can of salmon may also be added if desired.)

title: apricot chicken
directions: Rinse and pat dry the chicken thighs.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and place in a baking pan, skin side up.
Spread apricot preserves over chicken and sprinkle onion soup mix over that. Pour Russian dressing over everything and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: star-spangled punch
directions: Pour boiling water over cherry jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add cold water and stir.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Stir well. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Makes 16 (8-ounce) cups.

title: roasted red pepper dip
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients and blend well until smooth.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: sausage and cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Brown sausage in frypan.
Remove sausage, drain thoroughly. (Blot with paper towels to remove as mush grease as possible.)
In a double boiler, melt Velveeta cheese.
Then add oregano, thyme and sausage.
Mix well.
Spread on party bread.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes depending upon whether they are fresh or frozen.

title: caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in a large shallow pan.
Put it in a very slow oven (250°) to keep warm and crisp.
(If you want to use peanuts, sprinkle them into the popcorn that has been popped.)

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have 10-inch pie plate ready.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 7 ingredients.
Put in loaf pan. Cover with several bacon strips and tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: annie wingate's cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in fat.
Soften bread crumbs with broth to make moist.
Add onion, celery, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in greased casserole dish.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute broccoli, margarine and onion together.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well to serve later.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot. Cook slowly overnight or several hours.
Gravy can be thickened with cornstarch if desired.
Delicious with rice or noodles.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add vinegar, honey, salt, water and oil.
Add 4 cups flour and mix well.
Add yeast which has been softened in 1/2 cup water and 1/8 cup honey.
Add rest of flour and mix well. Knead until smooth and satiny.
Knead every 15 minutes for 3 times.
Fourth time, shape into loaves.
Cover and place in warm place to rise until double bulk, about 3/4 to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican grits casserole
directions: Combine water and salt in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Stir in grits.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix like cake and beat it.

title: beef stew
directions: Take only breasts of ptarmigan, salt and pepper and dip in beaten egg.
Roll in bread crumbs, then saute in butter or other shortening.
Place in roaster or Dutch oven.
Over this, pour 1 cup of sour cream and 2 tablespoons of wine.
Dust generously with paprika.
If desired, add 1 clove minced garlic.
Cook in oven at 350° until birds feel tender when pierced with a fork.
This whole bird may be cooked, but the breasts make a greater delicacy.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread into 2 glass pie plates (white looks better than clear).
Top with cut up vegetables and Cheddar cheese. Serve with Tostitos (chips).

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese together. Chop tomato, then add tomato and bacon bits. Chill. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Bring milk to boil.
Add marshmallows, stirring until marshmallows are melted; cool.
Add salt, vanilla and Cool Whip. Shave chocolate and add to rest of ingredients.
Put in graham cracker crust and add a few crumbs on top.

title: chocolate muffins
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in double boiler or in microwave. Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter, eggs and mix well. Add melted chocolate.
Stir.
Stir in unmelted pieces.
Spoon 2 tablespoons into muffin liners.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place crescent rolls on bottom of 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish. Sprinkle browned sausage on crescent rolls. Top this with hash browns. Mix milk with eggs and pour on top. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until set.

title: "stable boy shrimp"
directions: Put shrimp in pan to be used for cooking.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and oregano.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Place sliced butter on top.
Place under broiler, stirring often, until almost done (light pink).
Stir in bacon and broil about 1 minute or more for bacon. Sprinkle cheese over top and return to broiler until cheese is melted.
Good eating!

title: treasure chest dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and chopped egg.
Mix well. Add mayonnaise and garlic powder.
When warm, serve with chips or crackers.

title: spinach ricotta pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix spinach and onion; set aside.
Beat cheeses and seasonings in a small bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in spinach mixture. Spread into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with remaining ingredients (cheese and tomato).
Serve with bagel chips or crisp crackers.
Enjoy.

title: chilling chicken salad
directions: Line a round cake pan with waxed paper, sides and all.
Fold cheese and mayo. Add garlic powder, onion powder, seasoned salt and pepper. Add food coloring until light orange.
In another bowl, add chicken, eggs, celery, bell pepper, onions and grapes. Mix well.
Add cream cheese sauce (save 1/4 cup) and mix well. Pour into lined pan, filling evenly.
Take 1/4 cup sauce and add almonds.
Spread evenly on top of mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold with toast.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Take seeds and tops off peppers.
Mix in blender the onion, peppers and garlic.
Grate cheese.
Put all in a bowl and mix with mixer for 15 minutes.
Chill.
Good with Fritos.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and parboil potatoes and onions.
Place in casserole dish with cheese, salt and butter.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle crumbs and cheese over top and bake at 250° until bubbly and brown.

title: pork chops and potato dinner
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish with cover.
Place in bottom of dish 4 cups thinly sliced potatoes.
Pour over potatoes a mixture of cream of celery soup, evaporated milk, onions, salt and pepper. Trim fat from pork chops and brown chops on both sides in small amount of oil.
After browning, place chops on top of soup mixture and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Add in marshmallows and pecans. Spread in a buttered pan.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: velvet cream biscuits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; add whipping cream, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a well-floured surface and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a biscuit cutter or the mouth of a glass dipped in flour.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet; brush with melted butter and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and place in crock.
Add pickling lime and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain; rinse and then soak in ice water for 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, food coloring and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Simmer for 2 hours and then drain.
Make syrup out of 2 cups water, apple cider vinegar, sugar, red hots and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
For 3 days, drain off syrup and reheat, then pour back over cucumbers each day.
On day 3, heat cucumbers in syrup and pack in jars and seal.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel zucchini.
Cook in a little water until tender.
Drain. Put in blender and blend.
Measure 1 1/2 cups zucchini.
Put back in blender and blend together with the rest of the ingredients, except for cinnamon and nutmeg.
After blending, sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over the top.
Makes one 10-inch deep dish or two 9-inch pies.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, and then at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry tapioca
directions: Note: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix salad oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and water.
Combine ingredients.
Add 4 cups chopped apples and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1 small package butterscotch morsels on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: simple manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package directions; drain.
Place noodles in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles and sprinkle on mushrooms.
Top all with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated through and cheese is melted and starting to brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry pinwheel
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening to size of cornmeal.
Add milk; mix until soft dough is formed.
Roll out dough to 1/2 inch thick on a floured board. Spread with fruit and roll like a jelly roll.
Put syrup into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Cut dough roll into 1-inch slices and lay in syrup.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain, with ice cream or top with cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam then put your pecans and coconut on as a layer.
Next, pour cake mix on top, then your mixture of butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Drain berries and reserve juices.
Mash berries, add flour and juice.
Cook on medium-heat to boiling, add honey.
Simmer 5 minutes; add dash of lemon juice.
Remove from heat, will thicken as it cools.
This will work with any berries.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a large greased iron skillet and bake until done at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shirley's meat loaf
directions: Mix well 3/4 of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, onions, water and salt.
Shape into loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan or loaf pan.
Spread the remainder of the mushroom soup on top of the meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and core apples. Place layer of apples and layer of sugar in crock. Let stand overnight.
Place apple mixture and cinnamon in a large pan.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 hours.
Beat with rotary beater, spoon into jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: angel salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the whipping cream.
Mix well and put in freezer to thicken.
Fold in whipping cream and refrigerate.

title: sausage and rice dish
directions: Prepare rice mix as directed.
While rice is simmering, saute onion in butter.
Add sausage and brown slightly.
Set aside. Fold in sausage and onion to rice mix; add sour cream and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: marilyn's overnight hot dish
directions: Mix and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: george's green chile
directions: In 6-quart pan, fry pork and onions in cooking oil until well browned.
Add flour and water and continue cooking.
Add tomatoes, chiles, 1/2 can jalapenos, garlic salt, pepper and red pepper; simmer until pork is well done and tender, adding more water and flour as needed to thin or thicken.
Can thicken with cornstarch, if desired.
Serve over burritos, eggs, rice, etc.
Can make hotter by adding more jalapenos.

title: raisin pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Cool raisins a few minutes.
Let set.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over drained raisins and pour in pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: molly's breakfast casserole
directions: Trim bread crusts.
Butter each slice.
Arrange 8 slices of bread, buttered sides down, in bottom of well-buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with cheese.
Top with remaining slices of bread.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked indian pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, slowly stir cornmeal into hot milk. Cook over boiling water, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes. Preheat oven to 300°.
Lightly grease 2-quart (8 1/2-inch round) baking dish.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: In frypan, brown bacon.
Pour off some of the grease. Add onions, sugar, catsup and beans.
Cook on top of stove on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute ground beef with oil and onion until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: dark honey glaze(for ham, etc.)
directions: In a pot, start with dark molasses, water and cornstarch, adding other ingredients and bring to a simmer, then turn off heat.
Line baking pan with foil.
Place ham in pan.
Pour glaze over top, wrap in foil and place in oven.
Bake in oven at 350°, basting until done.
Enough for a 2 to 2 1/2 pound ham.

title: potato soup
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Cube potatoes, onion and carrot and put in big pot.
Add water, salt, pepper and butter.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Then add milk, turn heat down and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: low-fat eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box, using 1% or skim milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of pan and then pudding mix.
Continue to layer, ending with crackers.

title: stove top casserole
directions: Stir soups, milk and broccoli together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add torn up pieces of chicken or turkey on top of broccoli mixture.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions and spoon on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon raisin roll-ups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12 muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches.

title: colombia potato salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the potatoes.
Cut cold potatoes in uniform cubed pieces.
Add mixture to potatoes and refrigerate.

title: six layer dinner
directions: In a deep casserole, place potatoes.
Sprinkle with rice.
Add meat.
Add a layer of onions and a layer of carrots.
Cover with tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lo-applesauce raisin cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into a bowl.
Add oats and raisins.
Mix applesauce, oil, egg, vanilla and sweetener together.
Add to dry ingredients; mix just until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
(Two cookies equals 1 fruit and 1 fat for diabetics.)

title: five-hour stew
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in large casserole.
Combine tomato soup, mushroom soup and liquid from peas.
Pour soup mixture over casserole.
Toss lightly.
Cover.
Bake 5 hours at 275°.

title: mushroom lentil soup
directions: In a stockpot or large pot, combine broth, water, lentils, tomatoes, tomato paste, brown sugar, carrots, celery, onion and garlic.
Bring to a boil; lower heat.
Cover pot and simmer 30 minutes.
Add 1 cup sherry, pasta, mushrooms, spices and vinegar. Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving. Makes 12 to 13 cups.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Make a paste of the first 4 ingredients. Add 1 cup of boiling water and red food coloring. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Add lemon juice and oleo. Let cool. Mix strawberries. Pour into pastry shell and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut lean beef into 3/4-inch cubes; season with salt and pepper.
Flour, then brown in margarine.
Add onion, garlic, soups, mushrooms, broth and water.
Simmer for an hour or until beef is thoroughly tender.
Just before serving, stir in the Accent, sour cream and paprika.
Heat until just to the boiling point and serve over rice or Chinese crisp noodles.

title: french dip sandwiches
directions: Put ingredients in a crock pot.
Fill to the top with water. Cook 8-10 hours on low.
Shred/slice and serve on buns with juice on side.

title: chicken ratatouille(low-fat)
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Saute in wok the onion, pepper and eggplant in 1 tablespoon olive oil until soft (approximately 3 minutes).
Add zucchini and brown 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until soft (approximately 3 minutes).
Push veggies aside and add 1 tablespoon oil and cook chicken until brown (approximately 2 minutes).
Add garlic, herbs, salt and pepper. Cook until chicken is done and liquid evaporates (approximately 5 minutes).
Add lemon juice before serving.
Serve over fettuccini.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: In a pan, blend together soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic, ginger, wine and broth.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Flour sides of steak.
Brown in hot oil in a skillet.
Add all ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over low heat or in a 250 to 300 degree oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to cook down to a thick sauce.
Serves 6. Has a delicious smoked flavor.

title: rice stuffed flounder
directions: *Or use 1/4 teaspoon ground ginger.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain potatoes well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand or with a mixer.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix dressing and pour over cucumbers.

title: garden combo
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and basil in butter in a skillet just until vegetables are tender.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Add beans and carrots.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes, or until the vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine cornstarch and water, blending well.
Stir into vegetable mixture.
Add tomato; cook 1 minute, or until sauce thickens and tomato is thoroughly heated. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat the eggs at high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in the sugar. Stir in the pumpkin.
Add the lemon juice. Stir together the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Fold this into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased and floured sheet cake pan, 15 x 10-inches.
Top with finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on cup towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together.
Let cool, unfold and add filling.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add whipping cream, vanilla pudding and 1 quart of milk.
Microwave on High until thickened like pudding, stirring 2 to 4 times.
Stir in vanilla.
Let cool. Pour into freezer can and fill to indicated line with as much milk as needed.
Stir and freeze according to freezer's directions. Makes 6 quarts.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt sugar and margarine in skillet on low heat.
Before it gets hot add the egg.
Add dates and nuts. Cook on slow heat until mixture bubbles (2 or 3 minutes). Take off stove. Stir in Rice Krispies and vanilla. Spread coconut on waxed paper.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls on coconut. Roll in coconut and shape into balls.

title: cranberry cocktail
directions: Chill equal parts of cranberry juice and 7-Up.
Mix together just before serving.
Serve over ice or not.

title: saucy susan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a large baking dish with chicken breasts.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Add cut-up carrots, potatoes, etc.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 400°.
Baste often!!

title: taco salad
directions: Can make salad (except tomatoes and dressing) ahead.
Add tomatoes and dressing when ready to serve.

title: ravioli with ham and peas
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions.
Meanwhile, melt butter or heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and cook 2 minutes.
Add peas, cream and pepper. Bring sauce to boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add ham.
Drain cooked ravioli; toss in a large heated serving bowl with cream sauce and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: erica's cavatelli
directions: Saute chicken and green peppers in olive oil.
Add oregano, basil, parsley, hot pepper flakes, garlic salt, pepper, olives and tomatoes.
Simmer a few minutes, then add cavatelli and toss.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain cooked beans.
Place in 13 x 9 baking dish.
Saute onion in butter or oil.
Stir in cheese and cream of mushroom on medium heat until cheese is melted.
Add soy sauce.
Add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Pour over green beans.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.

title: garlic shrimp and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Saute garlic and shallots in butter mixture for 1 minute; add Chablis and brandy, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add mushrooms and cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer in shallow baking dish.
Pour butter-mushroom mixture over shrimp and broil for 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: calico potato salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients after chopping vegetables. Coarsely chop eggs, reserving 1 whole egg yolk.
Add chopped eggs to potato mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients, except yolk; toss with potato mixture.
Sieve reserved yolk over top.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot, put the chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Mix together.
Add chicken to the mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Turn to medium heat.
Put flour (small amount) on a plate. Flour each biscuit.
Cut biscuits into strips.
Add slowly to hot soup mixture.
Cook on medium heat until biscuits are no longer doughy (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).
Broth will get thick as it cooks.
If broth needs to be thicker, mix a little cornstarch with cold water and stir into the dumpling mixture.
Serves approximately 10 to 12.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: delicious lima beans
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add tomatoes, basil (to taste), salt and pepper (to taste) and tomato sauce.
Stir in lima beans. Pour mixture into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: robert's gingerbread
directions: Put molasses, butter and sugar into a mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and stir well.
Let cool.
Add nuts, raisins, flour (sifted with baking powder), spices and salt.
Beat the eggs well and add.
Turn into greased and floured shallow pan and bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares. Also good served warm, but handle carefully.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Arrange
pork chops in broiler pan, pouring ingredients over them.
Bake
at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn 2 to 3 times during
baking, basting with sauce.
Serve with rice, using sauce for gravy.

title: boo's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Put pecans in pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

To make an even, golden brown top, cut a strip of aluminum foil 30 inches long by 4 inches wide. Crimp this strip of foil around the rim of pie pan, forming a tent. Opening in center allows top to brown slower and crust not burn. Don't let foil touch top of filling.

title: horseshoe cookies
directions: Work Crisco into flour and salt.
Add other ingredients. Soften yeast in small amount of milk before adding to other ingredients.
Put dough in a greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: betty's jumbo cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,
except
raisins
and nuts.
Add raisins that have been boiled in 1 cup water for 3 minutes and cooled slightly.
Do
not
drain.
If dough is too stiff add a little water.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by large spoonfuls. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: overnight biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine dry ingredients, then add rest of the ingredients in given order.
Mix and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Roll out dough and cut biscuits, bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes until browned.
Dough not used can be refrigerated for up to 4 days.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter; add to other ingredients.
Bake in large pan because of rising.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon with a fork, removing bones.
Add eggs, breadcrumbs, butter and parsley.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Turn onto platter and slice carefully.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese.
Add vanilla and egg yolk; mix thoroughly.
Add cake mix, 1/3 at a time.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Can chill dough for 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and pour over sausage. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate milk
directions: Fill cup 1/2 full with mixture.
Add hot water.

title: sweet and sour turkey
directions: Rinse poultry.
In a 10-inch skillet combine juice concentrate, vinegar, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Bring to boiling.
Carefully add turkey.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Using a slotted spoon and fork transfer turkey to a carving board.
Remove the thigh bone.
Slice the meat.
Cover and keep warm.

title: perfection salad(sugarless)
directions: With spring just around the corner, a lot of us look forward to begin getting our gardens ready for planting.
Here is a way to plant a most successful garden this year.
I plan to dig in and get mine started.
Perhaps you'll want to do so, too.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients. Add egg and milk gradually; use mixer and beat until smooth.
Set aside.
Peel and core apples; cut into 1/3-inch slices.
Dip slices into batter; deep fry in vegetable oil at 375° until batter is golden brown. Remove; let cool, uncovered.
After fritters have cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix well and serve with sliced strawberries, cherries, apples, etc.

title: hamburg cheese bake
directions: Brown meat with salt, pepper, onion, green peppers and garlic salt.
Stir in oregano and tomato sauce.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature and blend with sour cream and cottage cheese. Put half the noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the cheese mixture over noodles.
Put rest of noodles on top, then put the meat mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine the ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: carrot sheet cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve juice and add water to make 1/2 cup. In bowl, combine liquids.
Add flour mixture until blended.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch or sheet cake pan for 25 to 40 minutes.
Spray pan with Pam.
Cool and frost with light cream cheese frosting if desired (recipe follows).
Makes 24 servings.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine until tender.
Blend in soup (unheated), milk, croutons and half of Cheddar cheese.
Put in oven until bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Add remaining cheese.

title: sweet cabbage slaw
directions: Bring all to a boil.
Pour over shredded cabbage.
Will keep a week in refrigerator, but is crisper after first day.

title: frikadeller
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients, except margarine, stirring well until light, airy and smooth.

title: date cookies
directions: Cook water, oleo and dates for 3 minutes and let cool.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Combine with cooled mixture.
Drop from spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine water, orange juice and rind.
Add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan for 20 minutes before removing.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions until done. Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain grease and add pizza sauce and mushrooms.
In a crock-pot, layer noodles, hamburger, sauce mixture, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and mix.
Add carrots and pineapple and mix.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured (3 layers) cake pans.
Cook in 350° or 375° oven for 30 minutes or so until done.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours or until thick.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into boiling water.
Boil for 2 minutes.
First boil one. If too soft, add a little more flour to dough.
Dough will be a little sticky.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, sugar, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Melt butter and chocolate separately; add to mixture. Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar and melted butter.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well. Add dash of salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large heavy pan, cook ground turkey
3 to 5 minutes, until no longer pink.
Add onion and saute 2 to 3 minutes longer, until softened. Add chili, celery, green pepper, corn, tomato sauce, honey and seasonings to turkey.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Stir one minute while boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/3 cup of butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: potato latkas
directions: Scrub potatoes very well and grate in food processor.
Some like them grated for a coarser texture and some just like them once grated for a coarser texture.
If you choose the finer texture, it doesn't work to just chop-you have to grate first. Finely chop the scallions.

title: squash supreme
directions: Butter a quart casserole dish.
Pour in half of the herb stuffing; pour in squash mixture.
Then add other half of herb stuffing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Place corn and beans in a 2 quart baking dish.	Sprinkle with pepper.
In mixing bowl, combine celery soup, sour cream, onion and cheddar cheese.
Pour on top of corn and beans.
Before placing in oven, pour melted margarine over top.
Sprinkle with crackers and almonds.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole dish in order and bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: bushel cookies
directions: Grind raisins and nuts together; mix together eggs, lard and sugar until creamy.
Add milk, soda, baking powder and Karo.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake in 375° to 400° oven until browned.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Chop into small pieces, celery, green onions, green peppers, green olives and black olives.
Toss ingredients together and sprinkle with the McCormick Salad Supreme.
Add Wishbone Italian dressing.
Mix and refrigerate. Serve cold and enjoy!

title: frederick's orange marmalade
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pastry for 1-crust pie as directed on package, except roll dough into rectangle, 12 x 9 inches.
Cut rectangle into 12 (3-inch) squares; prick with fork.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix (by hand) eggs, oil and sugar together.
Sift flour and add.
Add salt, nuts, bits and vanilla and mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch
pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool on cake rack and cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender in salted water.
Drain and mash. Mix squash with pimentos, carrots, 1/2 package of stuffing, cream of chicken soup, onions and sour cream.
Melt margarine and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Put remainder of stuffing on top of margarine.
Top with squash mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: standard pastry for a two crust pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until particles are size of small peas.
Sprinkle in water, one tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened and pastry almost cleans side of bowl.
Divide pastry into two balls and flatten and shape into 2 rounds on floured surface.
Roll pastry 2-inches larger than inverted pan.
Fold pastry into quarters; unfold and ease into pie pan, pressing firmly against bottom and side.
Fill and top with top crust and flute.
Don't forget to cut slits in top crust so steam can escape.
Cover edge with 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Take off during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake as recipe calls.

title: dennie's white pizza
directions: Preheat the oven to 500°.
Brush shell lightly with olive oil. Sprinkle on basil and garlic.
Arrange salami on shell. Sprinkle with onions. Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle tomatoes with Parmesan cheese.
Add pepper to taste. Sprinkle Mozzarella on top. Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: kona freeze
directions: Make sure ice cream is softened.
Mix 27 crushed Oreo cookies with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour ice cream over cookies.
Place in freezer and re-freeze.

title: noodle salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions on the package. Drain the noodles and add the onion, carrot and green pepper. Mix in a pan the vinegar, salt, garlic salt, oil and sugar. Bring this mixture to a boil; remove from heat and let cool. Pour over the noodles and add the celery seed. Refrigerate.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine hot water and poppy seed.
Mix remaining ingredients together, then add water and poppy seed mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a loaf pan.
Makes 2.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients into ground beef except tomato sauce.
Use only 1/3 cup in beef.
Set others aside.
Place meat loaf in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Take out of oven.
Drain grease.
Place remaining tomato sauce on top.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
In a large bowl, mix cake cubes and orange juice.
Arrange in prepared pan. Spread frozen ice cream evenly over cake.
Cover and freeze 1 to 2 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares.
Serve with strawberries and syrup.

title: grilled cheese pie
directions: Mix 2 ounces of the cheese with all of the other ingredients. Pour into a well-greased pie plate (or, if "doubling the recipe" use a cookie sheet).
Bake for about 30 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with the remaining 2 ounces of cheese and bake 2 minutes more.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: green chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions and chiles in butter; add soups.
Layer tortillas, deboned chicken, sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the best brownies
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in an 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: hamburger sloppy joes
directions: Stir and
fry hamburger and salt in skillet until done; drain. Return to	medium	heat.
Add the sauce; stir and heat until hot. Serve
on	hamburger
buns.
Feeds
to 6.
(One medium onion fried with hamburger is optional.)

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels and 1/2 cup milk in saucepan (set aside).
Mix other ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter into greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Pour chocolate chips, then pour caramel over baked batter. Top off with rest of batter and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted chews
directions: Place sugar and syrup in a pan.
Stir to combine.
Cook, stirring constantly, to a boil.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Special K.
Stir until coated.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool.

title: chicken cashew salad
directions: Toss with 1/2 cup Miracle Whip salad dressing and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut in lengthwise pieces.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers into clean, hot 1-pint jars.
Add about 2 tablespoons dill seed and 3 peppercorns to each jar.
Fill with pickling syrup to 1/2-inch of top of jar.
Adjust lids and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Remove jars from canner and tighten lids.
Makes 7 pints.

title: coconut date bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until coarse crumbs.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Press half of crumbs in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with filling.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: tomato-cheese fillets(microwave)
directions: Place margarine and onion in a 1-cup glass measure and cook on full power 1 1/2 minutes or until onion is soft. Arrange fish in a shallow baking dish with thicker edges of fish to outside of dish. Sprinkle salt and pepper over fish; cover with diced tomato pieces. Spread margarine and onions evenly over tomatoes. Cover with wax paper; cook 3 minutes on full power. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with waxed paper; cook 1 minute more or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Sprinkle with paprika. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet relish
directions: In medium glass bowl, toss cucumber and salt; cover and refrigerate 8 hours. Drain, then rinse in colander. In medium non-reactive saucepan, combine all ingredients, except mustard. Cook over low heat, stirring often, 20 minutes; stir in mustard. Cool to room temperature; store, covered, up to 2 weeks in refrigerator. Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Multiply recipe x 10 (10 times) for canning. Put in hot jars while hot and add hot sterilized lids.

title: chicken bake
directions: Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of pan.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and salt and pepper.
Mix canned soups with water and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cover for last 15 minutes if it gets too brown.
Serves 6.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour 1/2 batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Allow to cool.
Cook cabbage head until tender.
Combine ground beef, rice, onions and oregano.
Separate cabbage leaves.
Roll a small amount of ground beef mixture in the cabbage leaves, pressing leaves in on each end.
Place in a large slow cooker.
Pour tomato juice and drained sauerkraut over cabbage rolls.
Cook on medium for 3 hours.

title: swiss loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order given and press into loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350°.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Remove cake from oven. Let cool 5 minutes.
Poke holes in top of cake with end of a wooden spoon.
Fill each hole with milk and ice cream topping. Cool cake in refrigerator.
Top cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with candy bars on top of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Mix milk, orange juice, sugar, and ice cream in a blender. Serve immediately.

title: oriental peanut noodles
directions: Cook pasta; drain and keep warm.
In hot salad oil, cook green onions until tender.
In large bowl beat peanut butter and 1/4 cup hot water until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta and stir well.
Toss contents of bowl with pasta.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salty water.
Make sauce with cream of mushroom soup, milk and butter.
Grate cheese. Mix sauce with broccoli and layer rice, broccoli and grated cheese in casserole dish.
Repeat and bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix with other ingredients.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer uncovered until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook noodles.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 2 smaller pans.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs in large bowl using electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix on low until blended.
Turn into pan(s) and bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 (9 x 5-inch) loaf or 2 (5 5/8 x 3 1/8-inch) loaves.

title: glorified rice salad
directions: Combine rice, water, pineapple juice and salt. Mix to moisten the rice. Bring quickly to a boil over high heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add marshmallows, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Cool to room temperature. Fold in whipped topping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: butter-crumb potatoes
directions: Roll potatoes in melted butter, then in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Place in greased pan.
Pour any remaining butter over top.
Bake in 400° oven for 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Prepare pudding according to packaged directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put mixture in freezer can (1 gallon size) and finish filling with milk.
Freeze.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Add sugar and cream of tartar gradually to egg whites; beat until stiff.
Fold in soda crackers.
Add nuts and vanilla. Spread in long cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Cover with whipped cream or Dream Whip.
Spread cherry pie filling over top.

title: tart cherry salad mold
directions: Drain fruits, reserving liquid.
Add water to fruit liquid to make 3 1/4 cups.
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add fruit and ginger ale.
Chill until very thick, but not set.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into a 2-quart ring mold.
Chill until set.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Grease dish.
Layer shells and chicken, then spoon rice soup. Layer with cheese, then tomatoes and green chilies over cheese. Start over again, same as before.
End with grated cheese on top. Add extra liquid, if needed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
May be doubled for more people.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Boil onion and squash for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine in small bowl the sour cream, soup and carrots; add squash and onion mixture.
Add stuffing mix to melted margarine.
Pour 1/2 of the stuffing mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish, then pour the squash mixture on top of the bread mixture.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: honey oat bran bars
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, toss together cereal, nuts and raisins; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine the margarine, honey and brown sugar.
Stirring constantly, bring to a full boil 5 minutes.
Pour over cereal mixture; toss well to coat.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Beat thoroughly the oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add all the other ingredients and beat.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch greased pan. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Eat with milk as a breakfast cereal.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding to 3 cups milk, then add Cool Whip.
In a 11 x 13-inch pan, layer whole graham crackers.
Add half of pudding mixture; then add another layer of crackers.
Add remaining pudding, then crackers again.
Cover well with frosting. Refrigerate for a few hours before serving.

title: bacon cornbread
directions: In an ovenproof skillet, cook the bacon over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until it is crisp.
Remove bacon.
Leave fat in pan.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl, stir together the flour, cornmeal, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup of the milk; mix well.
Stir in the remaining 1/2 cup milk, corn and bacon and pour the mixture into the skillet on top of the fat.
Spread some of the bacon fat that has risen around the edge of the batter across the top with a spatula.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add cucumbers and onion.

title: texas brag
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in pan in this order; pour melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Cut off top of bread; make trough by removing insides.
Cook beef; drain off fat.
Add onion, bell pepper, soups and crumbled insides of bread to ground meat; mix well.
Stuff filling in bread trough.
Top with grated cheese.
Put top back on loaf.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs and salt and pepper. Form into 1-inch meatballs.
Place in a pan and place under broiler unit about 5 minutes, or until browned; drain grease.
In a Dutch oven, combine chili sauce, lemon juice and jelly; heat until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and simmer 30 minutes. Serve over rice.
Freezes well.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cinnamon sticky bread(makes one loaf)
directions: Break apart thawed dough and form into 2-inch balls.
Set aside in a warm place.
Melt butter and set aside.
In a shallow bowl, mix sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1/4 cup of melted butter in a small microwave bowl.
Add water and brown sugar.
Microwave at High for one minute until ingredients blend.

title: better than sex
directions: First mix together flour, butter and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: coconut orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape mixture into 1-inch round balls.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Yields 36 balls.

title: my famous irish pasta salad
directions: Boil package of pasta noodles as you normally would, strain water and let sit for about 7 1/2 minutes.
In a separate bowl mix all the other ingredients.
Then mix the noodles in with the ingredients and put in refrigerator for at least three hours for flavor to be totally absorbed.

title: wanda's cranapple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: 3-cheese meat pie
directions: Saute beef in hot oil until brown.
Drain off excess fat. Sprinkle cornstarch over meat and stir to combine.
In a bowl, whisk together milk, mayonnaise and eggs.
Add meat mixture, Cheddar cheese and green onions.
Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine and turn into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and the 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Measure 1 cup water and enough added to the dry ingredients to make a paste.
Blend into the paste 2 slightly beaten egg yolks, followed with the remainder of the water and one small can evaporated milk.
The mixture is cooked, stirring frequently, over a slow flame.
