One-fourth stick of butter is added during the cooking process and when the filling is thick, 1 1/2 teaspoons of vanilla is blended in.
The mixture is ready to pour into pastry shell.

title: pear salad
directions: Arrange pears in a casserole dish.
Make the lemon jello using the pear juice instead of water.
Blend the jello before it sets with softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Use the blender if necessary to get out lumps.
Pour this mixture over the pears and chill for several hours.

title: aunt helen's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and stir.
Stir in soda. Add everything else and mix.
Dough should be very stiff.
Drop golf ball sized balls on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Makes one 8 or 9-inch double crust.

title: chocolate cola frosting
directions: Combine butter, cocoa and cola beverage in a 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Microwave at High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in sugar and nuts.
Spread over hot cake.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Measure sugar, syrup and peanuts in 1-quart Pyrex.
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir; cook 3 minutes on High.
Add vanilla, salt and margarine.
Stir.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda. Stir well.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet and spread thin.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: judy's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Dip mushroom caps in oil and place in dish.
Chop very small mushroom caps and onions; saute in pan with butter and garlic.
When soft, pour into large bowl and mix with egg, sour cream and crabmeat (flaked).

title: dutch rhubarb dessert
directions: Spread rhubarb in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Mix white sugar, 1/4 cup flour and eggs well; pour over rhubarb.
Melt butter; add brown sugar and 3/4 cup flour.
Put on top of other mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Top with whipping cream or ice cream.
Serve hot or cold.
(Try apples or cherries.)

title: vinegar pie (circa 1959)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, eggs, vinegar and water.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly. Line pie pan with pastry and bake 5 minutes in moderate oven, 350°.
Then pour in filling and continue baking until crust is browned, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 small pie.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, layer bread, sausage and cheese in that order.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard and pour on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
May be made day before. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baby wipes
directions: Mix water and lotion until well blended.
Cut Bounty towels in half with a straight edge (sharp) knife.
Remove cardboard core from 1 roll.
Save the other roll for later use.
Place towels in an airtight container (Tupperware Signature Series 3 works great). Pour water mixture over towels.
Let set several hours.
Pop up towels from center and enjoy.

title: beef consomme soup rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Amounts will vary according to pan size.
Make crust by pressing rolls to cover pan.
Top with bacon or sausage.
Pour beaten eggs, enough water to cover.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until eggs are set.

title: benedictine
directions: Mix all of above ingredients together and tint pale green with food coloring, if desired.
Use as a dip or a sandwich spread.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix warm water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand about 5 minutes. Add shortening and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Knead about 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and bubbles form under dough.
Let rise about 45 minutes in warm place. Punch down and shape into rolls.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise for about 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Rolls will have a hollow sound when thumped gently on bottom when done.

title: microwave chicken
directions: In a microwave-safe casserole dish, add the tomatoes, onions, green pepper, white wine, parsley and oregano.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add the chicken breasts.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and green onions. Spread mixture on each tortilla, then place ham slices on top. Now roll each tortilla up and wrap separately in plastic wrap. Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer lettuce, onion, green pepper, cauliflower, peas, radishes, mushrooms, mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar, salad dressing, bacon bits and Cheddar cheese.
Cover in foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: vegetable cheese medley
directions: In the microwave, heat the bag of cauliflower, broccoli and mixed veggies until tender.
Drain off excess water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stir, sprinkling cheese throughout.
Melt cheese to desired cheese taste.
Sprinkle some cheese on top. Serve hot.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in 1 cup water in large bowl for several minutes. Mash bread with fork.
Add beef, onions, parsley, cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Pour on tomato sauce; sprinkle with oregano and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add sugar, cereal and rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Store in refrigerator. (Keeps for weeks.) Take out amount needed.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: broccoli and bacon quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with some of the beaten eggs and prick crust with a fork.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Mix and stir remaining ingredients until well blended.
Put into baked crust.
Bake at 250° for about 40 minutes or until firm.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Just mix and serve.
Use 1/3 cup mix with one mug of water.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Brown meat in skillet; put in baking dish.
Mix soup and water; pour over meat.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.
Serve on rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: swedish bullas
directions: Scald
milk.
Cool
to
lukewarm.
Add
sugar,
melted butter, salt, yeast cake and
the eggs.
Stir in cardamon seed and flour to mix. Turn out
on	floured
board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in
greased bowl and let rise until double in size.
Turn out and
tie
in
bowknots or braid into two loaves. Ice, if
desired.
Bake
at 375° approximately 30 minutes.

title: self crust egg custard
directions: Soften oleo. Mix oleo, sugar and flour. Add eggs. Gradually add milk and flavoring. Pour into large ungreased pie plate. Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon if desired. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: dutch honey
directions: Bring to full boil.
Let boil 1 minute.
Great syrup for pancakes and waffles.
A family favorite for many years.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain and combine beans.
Add onions and peppers.
Mix the balance of the ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Toss and chill overnight or for a comparable time.
Toss again to coat ingredients and drain.

title: cajun back ribs
directions: Combine all seasoning ingredients together well and dust all surfaces of ribs with mixture.
Prepare medium-hot coals in covered grill, banking coals when hot.
Grill ribs over indirect heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning every 15 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine butter, sugar, honey or corn syrup and molasses in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Scrape mixture into a large bowl and let cool.

title: sue's refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and shortening; heat until melted.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Add dry yeast.
Let stand one hour.
Then add enough self-rising flour to make a fairly stiff dough.
Let rise until double in size, then work down and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours.
Then take out and bake in a greased pan at 350° until done.

title: honey roast turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove giblets and neck from turkey. Rinse turkey and drain.
Place turkey, breast side down, on rack in roasting pan.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix croutettes, water, salad dressing and margarine.
Beat eggs slightly with 1 cup of milk.
Add to stuffing mixture.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and salt.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend soup and remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pasta with peas (spaghettini con piselli)
directions: Set 6 quarts of water to boil, with 2 tablespoons of salt; this may take half an hour.
Add the spaghettini and cook for 7 or 8 minutes, or until done, but still firm.
In a large skillet, heat the oil and add the ham, onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook until the onion is soft.
Add the broth and the peas, which have been partially cooked, but still should be quite firm.
Cook until the peas are almost done, then add the tomatoes and basil, salt and pepper to taste and cook for 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Drain the spaghettini and turn into warm bowl.
Add the sauce and the butter and half the cheese.
Toss gently and serve at once with the remaining cheese on the side.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain and cool.
Add next 5 ingredients.
One-half hour before serving, add taco chips and chill.

title: winter punch
directions: Place cinnamon sticks and cloves in cheesecloth and heat with cranberry juice in large pan; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool, remove spice bag.
Pour into punch bowl, add vodka and ginger ale.
Float block of ice.
Makes 24 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add strawberries; mix real good. Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish. Let jell. When it jells, spread sour cream. Then add other ingredients and let jell. Good as a sweet.

title: peach crisp
directions: To make the topping, mix the flour and sugars in a bowl.
Cut the butter into small pieces; mix it into the flour by rubbing it into the mixture with fingertips.
Add walnuts.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut peaches in half, peel and remove pits.
Cut into slices.
Mix with flour and sugar (to taste).
Spread peaches in a 2-quart glass or ceramic ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle topping over peaches.
Bake until topping is brown and peaches are bubbly. You can serve with heavy cream.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast at 300° covered 1/2 hour per pound.	Cool and slice.
Reserve broth, skim off grease. Add thyme, worcestershire sauce, garlic, marjoram, green peppers, onions, and hot sauce. Simmer till pepper and onion are done.
Add sliced beef and heat. Cool and marinate for several days.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until the meat is lightly browned.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into an 8-inch square casserole dish.
Shred cheese and sprinkle over meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, saving liquid.
Melt butter, blend in cornstarch. Add beet juice and stir constantly over direct heat until sauce comes to a boil and thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and beets, continue heating slowly until beets are hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter. Mix all ingredients together. Place in a baking dish and bake for 60 minutes at 350 degrees. For a more moist casserole do not drain the whole kernel corn.

title: sopa de fideo
directions: Preheat electric skillet.
Melt Crisco and saute vermicelli until lightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Add beef and cook, stirring, until meat loses red color.
Stir in all but cheese. Stir together gently.
Set skillet temperature to 200° and cover and simmer mixture for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and place cheese on top.
Cover and cook another 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Arrange berries in crust.
Mix cornstarch and water; cook until thick.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over fresh berries in crust.
Keep cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spinach salad
directions: Drain water chestnuts and combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Serve with dressing below after mixing ingredients:

title: stir-fry chicken and peppers
directions: Using electric frypan or wok, place on high heat.
Add oil and then garlic.
Cook for 1 minute.
Stir.
Add scallions and cook for 1 minute longer.
Continue stirring.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Lay the tortilla chips on a cookie sheet.
Toss together the cheese, chilies and onion and sprinkle over the tortilla chips.
Bake for about 5 minutes until the cheese has melted.
Serve hot!

title: lefse (norwegian bread)
directions: Beat instant potatoes into the other ingredients except flour. Cool thoroughly (overnight).
Work in flour; form into a thick roll.
Divide into 16 pieces.
Cover and refrigerate.
Take out a few pieces at a time to roll out and bake on a dry griddle.

title: bean casserole
directions: Add all beans to hamburg, bacon and onion.
Add sugars, catsup, mustard and molasses.
Bake in casserole at 350° for one hour in preheated oven.

title: taco salad(dip)
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning together. Spread mixture on 12-inch platter; put platter in freezer for 10 minutes to allow mixture to thicken.
Remove platter from freezer and place shredded lettuce on outer edge of platter; place tomatoes on top of lettuce, then place sliced olives on top of tomatoes.
Stand nacho chips around edges of platter and replace as needed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugars, spices and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and Jell-O together; add hot water. Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Cool and pour over berries that have been sliced and put into cooked crust.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: Toss beef strips with flour.
Add oil to heavy skillet and brown beef well.
Add Worcestershire sauce and sherry.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add steamed vegetables and cooked Chinese egg noodles or spaghetti.
Toss with beef and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: dried beef sandwich filling
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and process on grind until smooth.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour in 2 greased long pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and frost cake with coconut cream cheese frosting.

title: cream sauce - microwave(medium sauce)
directions: Place butter in 4-cup glass measuring cup and melt in microwave.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend in milk gradually. Cook in microwave on Roast for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened. Stir 3 or 4 times during cooking.
Can season with sherry.

title: ellen's squash muffins
directions: Mix shortening, squash and sugar. Sift together flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix soda and milk. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and soda.
Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: "reese" krispy treats
directions: Mix together the Karo syrup and sugar and heat to boiling. Time for exactly 30 seconds, starting as soon as bubbles appear. Remove from heat.
Mix peanut butter into the hot sugar mixture. Pour over the Rice Krispies cereal.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt the milk chocolate morsels in the microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread over the cereal mixture.

title: quick steak and onions
directions: Cook onions very slowly in 2 Tbls. oil until golden brown. Remove to warm platter.
Increase heat and quickly brown steaks in remaining oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange on hot platter.
Stir flour into drippings and add water or milk stirring constantly until gravy boils.
Serve onions and gravy over steaks.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Cook beef, broth, water, bay leaves, tomato sauce and pepper for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add linguica, potatoes, carrots, celery and cabbage.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Combine first six ingredients until well mixed.
Shape into 48 small meatballs.
Cut Mozzarella into 48 cubes (1/2-inch.) Push a cheese cube into the center of each meatball, covering the cheese completely with the meat.
Roll each meatball lightly in the flour.
Cook the meatballs in oil in a large skillet until browned.
Drain.
Add pizza sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until meatballs are no longer pink.
Serve over pasta or rice , in buns or as an appetizer.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions with 1/2 cup water until brown. Drain excess fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.

title: chicken 'n chipped beef
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with crumbled chipped beef.
Wrap breasts in bacon and put on top of beef.

title: strawberry-rhubarb gelatin
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring rhubarb and water to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until rhubarb is tender. Remove from heat. Add the gelatin powder, sugar and jam; stir until gelatin is dissolved. Add pineapple juice. Chill until partially set. Stir in apple and nuts. Pour into serving dish. Chill until set. If using a mold, coat with nonstick cooking spray before pouring in mixture.

title: nutty brown rice
directions: Saute rice and onions in butter until golden.
Stir in broth and salt.
Bring to a boil; stir once.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes, or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Add nuts; toss lightly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package.
Mix soups, margarine and milk together until heated.
Pour in noodles and heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
For more chicken, add 2 cans chunky chicken.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in covered casserole at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions fine.	Add all other ingredients and all ingredients are chopped fine.
Mix all together and let set several hours (overnight is better).

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli up fine.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add vegetables.
Let stand six hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: ilona's sticky buns
directions: You will also need 1 Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamed potatoes(this recipe is especially good with fish.)
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and slice.
Place potatoes in baking dish.
Make sauce by melting the butter in a double boiler.
Add flour, salt, pepper and onion juice; blend thoroughly.
Pour in cold milk and stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour sauce over potatoes, cover dish and bake in a 350° oven for 20 more minutes without stirring or basting.
Serves 6.

title: nana's choco chip coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, margarine, sour cream, baking soda in large bowl on low speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Add vanilla, beat well for a few minutes.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed; drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot dressing over drained vegetables.
Cool.
Add peppers, onion and celery. Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to use. Keeps up to 2 weeks.
Makes 15 to 16 servings.

title: pull-apart yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the milk, margarine or butter, sugar and salt.
Add the flour.
Knead.
Allow to rise in bowl until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Punch dough down.
Roll out into an 8 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread surface with soft margarine. Cut into halves; stack halves, then cut into fourths.
Stack layers sideways in medium loaf pan which has been greased.
Allow to rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pull apart to serve.

title: caesar pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and cool. Add broccoli, cauliflower, cucumber and red bell pepper.
Toss salad with salad dressing.
Add Parmesan cheese and chill.
To serve, squeeze lemon juice over salad.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley.

title: lobster newberg
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter; add sherry, then lobster meat and heat gently.
In double boiler, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add flour and whisk briskly to get rid of lumps.
Add cream and stir.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Mix egg yolks in a bowl.
Stir about 1/4 cup white sauce into the eggs.
Mix and return to the pan with remainder of white sauce.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Add lobster mix and heat through gently.
Do not boil or it will curdle.

title: egg in a frame
directions: Cut a hole in the center of the bread with an upside down drinking glass.
Then melt one pat of butter in a small frying pan over low heat.
Toss in the bread and break the egg into the hole. Don't worry if you break the yolk.
Cook until the bread is golden brown on the bottom.
(You can peek with a spatula.)
Turn the bread over.
Put the remaining butter in the pan and use your spatula to make sure it gets under the toast.
Continue frying until the egg looks done.
No more than a couple of minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Add sliced apples and nuts. Spread mixture into 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg, breadcrumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add beef; mix well.
Press over bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Cook in microwave on High 3 minutes; set aside.

title: crab canape
directions: Combine ingredients; set aside for spread.
Cut circles of bread for eloquence and spread crab mixture on each circle. Broil until hot.
Serve hot.
These appetizers may be made several hours ahead of time and refrigerated until time to broil.

title: coconut cookies or chocolate chips
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda, alternating with milk.
Add coconut or chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake. Remove from oven when cookie start to go down.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Mix with other ingredients.

title: microwave mock chinese casserole
directions: Combine soup mix and water in 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole. Cover with lid.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes until mixture boils. Stir in rice and let stand covered.
Crumble sausage in 1-quart casserole.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Microwave 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes or until set, stirring once.
Drain thoroughly. Stir in rice mixture.
Cover.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: maryland corn oysters
directions: Beat egg until smooth.
Add corn, flour, seasoning, butter and enough milk to make a thick batter.
Grease the frying pan to cover the bottom.
Drop batter by spoonfuls, about the size of a fried oyster.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well; chill.
(May use bananas and/or peaches.)

title: creamy pecan fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and butter; set aside.
Combine sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook 9 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over chocolate mixture, stirring until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Add pecans; stir until well blended.
Spread mixture in a lightly buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Chill until firm and cut into squares.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: sweet and sour carrot salad
directions: Peel and slice carrots and cook until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and add remaining ingredients while carrots are warm.
Let stand overnight.
Serves 15-20.
Can be served cold, hot, or room temperature.

title: chicken sensational
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and toasted, sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fettuccine with butter sauce
directions: Bring water and 1 tablespoon of salt to a rolling boil in a large pot.
Cook fettuccine until just al dente.
While fettucine is cooking, melt butter in a saucepan.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and garlic.
Simmer together on very low heat.
Sprinkle drained fettuccine with cheese.
Pour butter sauce over all and serve.

title: fish sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve over fish.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and measure.
Add soda and spices and sift twice more.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with blackberries.
Pour into 2 well greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jane's shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine, then add rest of ingredients.
Cook just until shrimp are done.
Serve over rice.
Serve with buttered broccoli and lemon pie.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger meat, seasoned to taste with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add tomato paste.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cook noodles, then put in baking dish, alternating the noodles, meat and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
Beat together remainder of ingredients until smooth.
Pour 1/2 batter in tube pan, greased and floured.
Add 1/2 apple slices.
Add remainder of batter; then finish with apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Prepare a thick mush of 2 1/2 cups salted water.
Put water in microwavable 2-quart measuring cup or casserole dish.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in 3/4 cup cornmeal mixed in 1-cup cold water. Continue to microwave stirring every minute until mush thickens. Remove and season with garlic powder and chili powder to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; cook until thick.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites; add 3 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with other mixture.
Pour in 2 standard loaf pans. Bake at 325° for up to 1 hour.
Check at 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour in frying pan.
Add egg yolks and 2 cups milk.
Stir over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla, stir until butter is melted.
Pour into pie crust.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients gently, but thoroughly, in a casserole dish. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour. Good warm or cold.

title: chewy date torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, butter and vanilla.
Stir just until combined.
Stir in dates and nuts. Pour into a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pudding tests done.
Cool and cut into squares. Top with whipped cream and additional nuts if desired.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Thaw and cook the spinach without adding water, about 5 to 8 minutes. Saut onions and artichokes in butter. Add softened cream cheese to spinach and stir well. Add salt, Tabasco, artichoke/onion mix and 1/2 of Parmesan cheese to spinach and stir. Place in a buttered baking dish, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 20 minutes in preheated 400° oven. Serves 6 to 8.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Melt 1/2 cup oleo in baking dish.
Mix potatoes, onion, cheese, sour cream and soup.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix corn flakes with 1/2 cup oleo.
Remove casserole and sprinkle corn flake mixture over the top.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: banana nut pound cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Sift dry ingredients; add with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add mashed bananas.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook all ingredients, except shrimp, until thick.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: overnight bean salad
directions: Combine beans, onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: unsalted soda cracker dessert
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tarter, slowly add sugar.
Add crackers, walnuts and vanilla and beat until well mixed.
Spread batter in a greased glass 13 x 9 inch baking
dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 - 35 minutes.
Cool this crust.
Top with Cool Whip, then top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, peanut butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix flour and soda together and add to mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add M&M's and mix until M&M's are evenly distributed through dough.
Place drops on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until very light brown.
Let cool before taking off sheet.
Makes a bunch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, milk, onion and egg. Reserve 2/3 cup bread crumbs for topping. Stir remaining crumbs into corn mixture. Place in buttered dish. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Pour melted butter over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Fold in cornbread mix, creamed corn and cheese.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Pour cheese dip on top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat together in thick saucepan or double boiler the chocolate, dry ingredients, egg yolks and one-half of the milk. Stir and mix well. Add rest of milk and stir and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla. Pour in pie shell and cover with meringue. Cook at 350° until meringue is ready.

title: red lettuce salad(quick, goes with everything)
directions: Use oil and red wine vinegar dressing or Good Seasons sesame soy.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Pour melted butter and Karo over fruit and nuts.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Let stand overnight.

title: easy swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, egg, crumbs and seasoning.
Form into balls. Melt cranberry sauce, water, soup and chopped onion in large pot. Bring to a boil, then lower heat.
Drop in meatballs.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Pour over rice, noodles or chopped boiled potatoes.

title: fluff
directions: Add oranges to cottage cheese along with drained pineapple and mix well.
Sprinkle the jello powder over the cottage cheese and blend well.
Fold in whipped toping and chill for 2 hours.

title: crunchy tossed salad
directions: Makes: 4 entre salads at $3.41 each (or 6 side salads).

title: upside-down ham casserole
directions: Combine the brown sugar with melted butter; pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover bottom of pan with pineapple and ham. Place pan in heated oven at 400° while preparing rice mixture. Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring.
Spread over pineapple and ham. Cover and bake 10 minutes.
Invert on serving dish.

title: orange butter frosting
directions: Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add rind.
Add juice a few drops at a time, alternately with more sugar until right consistency to spread.
Frosting may be varied in flavor by substituting 5 tablespoons of your favorite jelly or preserves for the orange juice.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Melt the margarine and mix with graham crackers and nuts. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, marshmallows and sugar. Let set overnight. Three hours before serving, add remaining ingredients. Mix all together.

title: hot cajun potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes (boil).
Strain, place in crock or heavy bowl that will hold heat.
Heat green beans in potato water.
Drain. Heat oil until hot.
Slice onion.
Cube potatoes with knife. Place green beans over potatoes.
Place onion (separated) over green beans.
Sprinkle vinegar over onions.
Salt and pepper. With hot oil, drizzle over onions.
(If onions don't sizzle, oil isn't hot enough.) Mix gently!
Serve hot.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut partially frozen cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices slightly overlapping on a pizza pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool slightly and loosen from pan.
Allow to cool on the pan. Combine cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Chill; cut into slices or wedges with pizza cutter.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until tender; remove from heat.
Mix everything together.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Bake uncovered for 15 minutes longer.

title: ms. gregory's quick supper
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and set aside.
Saute pepper and onion. Return meat to skillet.
Add soup and 1 can water.
Simmer.
Great served over slab of homemade bread toasted in oven and cole slaw.

title: pecan roll
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers real fine and mix all ingredients together.
Roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice as needed.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine sour cream, soda and eggs; beat well for 2 or 3 minutes.
Sift flour, then resift with baking powder and salt. Stir into creamed mixture with sugar; beat until smooth.
Put in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.

title: fruit bars
directions: Put in well-greased and floured pan, all but 1 or 1 1/2 cups of batter.
This is sort of thick.
It will seem thin in thickness.
Spread 1 can of pie filling over dough.
Then add the rest of batter over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: 2 cheese logs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into logs.	Roll in pecans. Refrigerate.

title: fudge
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar; mash lumps out.
Add cream.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove.
Beat in margarine and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and walnuts.
Beat until ready to pour.

title: brownies
directions: Put all margarine and cocoa in saucepan until margarine melts; remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Stir in eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Add flour mix.
Put in pan and bake 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Cut the first 4 ingredients in small chunks. Add the peas and bacon bits.

title: five ingredients salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Remove outer leaves and use heart of cabbage, cut fine.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender but not soft.
(Cook uncovered to retain natural color; drain.)
Make a medium white sauce as follows: melt butter, add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth; add milk gradually and cook until smooth and glossy. Add cabbage and white sauce.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs after pouring into greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until nicely browned (about 20 minutes).

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix well and spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocoholic's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix wafers and butter together. Press into bottom of springform pan.
Bake 10 mins.
Mix cream cheese, 1/4 c. sugar and vanilla.
Add 2 beaten
egg yolks
and melted chocolate bits.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Gradually add remaining sugar.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Whip heavy cream and fold into mixture.
Pour over crumb crust and freeze. Decorate with additional whipped cream, if desired.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 4 tablespoons cold water; add boiling water, lemon juice, pineapple with its juice and sugar. Refrigerate until this mixture starts to jell.
Rub the crust off the angel food cake and tear half of the cake into small pieces. Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip 2 envelopes of Dream Whip and add to gelatine mixture; pour over cake in pan.
Tear up remainder of the cake, put over top and press down lightly.
Whip remaining 2 envelopes Dream Whip, top the cake with this and sprinkle with coconut.
Chill overnight.

title: grandma gonzales' salsa
directions: Boil the peppers for 10 minutes; drain and cool.
Rinse and stem cilantro.
Stem cooled peppers.
Put all ingredients in blender; blend until mixture is smooth.
Remember:
The more peppers used in the mixture, the "hotter" it will be.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground round and onions; put in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on high 4 to 6 hours.

title: quick and easy cioppino
directions: In a Dutch oven or deep skillet, heat olive oil and saute onion over medium heat until soft and golden, 10 minutes.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
This makes a thin dough.
Let rise 15 minutes, covered.
Pour into bread pan or spoon into muffin pan.
Let rise 15 more minutes.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Brush tops with butter.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown floured steak
on
both
sides; do not cook done. Layer steak, potatoes,
onions
and
bell
pepper.
Pour soups over and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks. Place brown sugar, slightly beaten egg yolks, pumpkin, milk, salt and spices in saucepan. Simmer until thickens.

title: joyce sann's salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and lime jello in one cup of hot water, then add one cup cold water.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Mix well and put into refrigerator until firm.
Serve in lettuce cups.

title: fruit nut muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a large mixing bowl. Add beaten egg, milk and oil. Stir until just blended. Mix in chocolate bits, drained pineapple, chopped nuts and drained cherries.
Pour batter into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until they test done.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: nonfat homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine hot water and sugar in blender and blend 1 minute, pulsing on and off or until sugar has partially dissolved.
Add milk powder slowly with blender running.
(Can also mix at high speed with electric mixer.)
Store, covered in refrigerator, if not used immediately.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Add milk and clams.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook slowly about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add chili powder to taste.

title: venison steak
directions: Soak venison in milk
for
minutes.
Dip in egg and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry
in
skillet
with
more oil than usual. When brown, remove
from oil and place in baking dish. Pour mushroom soup over and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix together; season to taste with salt and white pepper. Serves 8.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt caramels with 1/3 c. evaporated milk in a small pan set over medium heat, stirring constantly (or microwave mixture on medium, stirring twice, until melted, about 2 1/2 minutes). Set aside.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Brown beef cubes.
Boil potatoes, carrots, corn and peas in a pot of water.
Add beef cubes.
Pour 2 cups of water into the frying pan that you browned the beef in.
Boil it.
Then pour it into the pot with the potatoes, carrots, peas, corn and beef.
Mix cornstarch and water in a jar; shake it.
Add, a little at a time, to thicken the gravy.

title: francis' chocolate logs
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, extract, coconut, pecans and cracker crumbs into peanut butter.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Blend well.
Shape into logs and dip in chocolate and paraffin that have been melted together.
Put on wax paper to dry.
Store in refrigerator.

title: greek pasta salad with shrimp and olives
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients in large bowl. Add linguine and shrimp; toss to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Let stand at room temperature.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Boil all vegetables in 1 quart water for 30 minutes.
Add Velveeta and soups; simmer until cheese melts.
(Watch and stir often to prevent burning on the bottom of pan.)
When all melted, add milk.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic in oil.
Add celery, soup and thawed vegetables.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Turn into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and let bake 25 minutes at 350°. Remove cover and top with noodles.
Return to oven for 5 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: almond rocca
directions: Melt butter and sugar, stirring constantly, until lemon pudding like consistency.
Continue cooking (it will separate) until smooth caramel color (hard crack stage).
Put in whole almonds.
Pour into greased pan (cookie sheet).
Spread.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Put in freezer.
Take out just before serving.
Break into pieces.

title: curried chickpeas (churna)
directions: Saute chopped onion in oil until lightly cooked and soft.
Add curry and stir.
Add salt and garlic.
Add chickpeas with water from can.
Stir and add tomato.
Simmer about 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add warm water if sauce becomes too thick.
Before serving, add chopped coriander.
Can be served over rice or with nan.

title: swedish pancakes(these are like little crepes)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Beat in milk.
Add salt and sugar; mix well. Add flour a little at a time and mix well.
Heat a large smooth-bottomed frying pan over medium heat.
Add a bit of oil to prevent sticking.
Then pour in just enough mix to cover the pan bottom in a thin layer (pick up the pan and roll it to distribute the pancake).
When the top of the pancake looks almost dry to the touch, run a spatula around the edge to loosen it and turn it over.
The pancake should be a nice medium brown.
Remove from the pan once the bottom is also cooked (this takes less time than cooking the first side).
Stack finished pancakes on a plate in a warm oven and serve once they're all cooked.
As each pancake is taken, spread butter, jam, fruit, applesauce, yogurt, syrup or anything else that sounds good down the middle of each cake and roll it up.
Enjoy!

title: dried beef dip
directions: Use equal parts sour cream and cream cheese.
Use approximately 2 teaspoons minced onion for 1/2 pint sour cream and 3 ounces cream cheese.
Add dried beef to taste.

title: raisin and nut pastry
directions: Cut butter or margarine and cream cheese.
Add flour. Refrigerate several hours.
Make 1 inch balls, then flatten, fill and fold into crescents.

title: gooey cake
directions: Cook butter and cocoa in double boiler until it boils.
Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add cocoa mixture.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Mix well; pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with marshmallows and return to oven to brown.
Remove from oven and pour icing over hot cake.

title: diabetic graham cracker pie crust
directions: Roll graham crackers with rolling pin to crush.
Add melted oleo and mix well with a fork.
Set aside 2 tablespoons for garnish.
Press crumbs into a pie plate evenly.
Chill 3 hours before filling.

title: cherry-cake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix fudge cake mix, almond extract, cherry pie filling and beaten eggs; beat with mixer until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool 1 to 2 hours before frosting.
Let frosting set before cutting into bars.

title: baked chicken with tarragon sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Arrange in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done. Chill 1 hour.
Combine mayonnaise, celery and tarragon. Set aside.
Remove stems from spinach. Wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry.
Arrange spinach on individual plates. Arrange chicken and tomato wedges on top of spinach.
Spoon mayonnaise mixture over chicken. Garnish, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit (except apple rings, which can be discarded) and save juice.
Cook sugar, cornstarch, juice and margarine until thickened.

title: italian tortillas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, spinach, Ricotta cheese and egg.
Place approximately 1/2 cup mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll tightly; arrange seam side down in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and basil; spoon over filled tortillas.
Sprinkle with rest of Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: delicious cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, pimentos and green peppers.
In a saucepan, mix first five ingredients, bring to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
This will keep for two weeks in refrigerator.
Great on hot dogs.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pudding and pie spice; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine milk, egg and pumpkin.
Blend until smooth.
Add spice and pudding.
Stir until lumps are gone.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, pecans and raisins.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: crabmeat dip (hot) #3
directions: In a double boiler, melt the cream cheese and butter.
Add crabmeat and seasonings.
Serve in a chafing dish and serve with crackers or in small patty shells.

title: taro cakes(meatless)
directions: Combine taro, baking powder and sugar and a small amount of water.
Mix until smooth, form into small cakes with wet hands. Place on buttered pan.
Make a small depression in each cake and press in a generous amount of butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: Crush vanilla wafers to make crust.
Save enough whole wafers to stand up around the inside of pie pan.
Mix together egg yolks, lemon juice and condensed milk.
Pour into pie crust.
Use egg white for meringue.
Put in refrigerator until served.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 quart milk, 1 cup rice and raisins in double boiler.
Steep until rice is done. Bring to boil 1/2 quart milk.
Beat eggs gently and add remaining sugar.
Pour hot milk into beaten egg mixture and add vanilla. Combine and fold gently egg mixture into rice mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon. Place casserole in shallow pan of water.
Bake 1 hour until custard is set at 350°, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chili dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks in a saucepan.
Add chili.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
A small can of Ro-Tel may be added if desired.
Keep warm in a small crock-pot. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Season and cook chicken in enough water that there will be 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Chop and saute peppers and onions in oleo. Cook spaghetti in broth, mashed tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce until thickened, not too long. Add peas and mushroom soup.
Add shredded cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste. Remove bones from chicken and add to other mixture.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in 1 bowl. Combine shortening, eggs and milk in separate bowl.
Add dry ingredients after you combine shortening mixture; add a little at a time while mixing.
After the batter is mixed, fold in coconut. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper.
Put half of stuffing in casserole and add meat and carrots.
Mix sour cream and soup and pour over carrots. Top with stuffing.
Put in layers the stuffing, meat, carrots, soup and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: kathy's breadmaker kolaches
directions: Place ingredients in breadmaker pan with yeast on top of dry ingredients.
Start machine on dough cycle.
After 20 to 30 minutes, cut off machine, open lid and mix lightly with wooden spoon until all dry ingredients are mixed in.
Close and restart on dough cycle.
After cycle is over, let dough rise to top of pan.

title: crab alaska
directions: Combine chili sauce, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, lemon juice and chives.
Taste; adjust seasonings, paying special attention to the horseradish and lemon, because these vary in intensity.
Set the cream cheese on a serving platter.
Mound the crab on top.
Pour the sauce over.
Serve with French bread, crackers, or Melba toast.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and creamy.
Add other ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish or pan.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Freeze well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from meat and rub with garlic.
Sprinkle meat with some of the flour and pound.
Turn meat and repeat.
Continue until you have used as much flour as the meat will hold.
Cut meat into 6 pieces.
Place in a nonstick casserole.
Cover with vegetables, tomatoes and beef stock.
Cover casserole and cook at 300° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve meat and mashed potatoes with Basic Bouillon Gravy.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake and icing
directions: Mix the cake mix according to package.
Bake in 3 layers, then put one in punch bowl after cooled.
Mix the egg whites, cold water, honey or Karo syrup, sugar, salt and strawberries.
Put all in double boiler.
Beat constantly until fluffy.
Frost first layer in punch bowl, then add another layer of cake and frost it. After last layer of cake, add all frosting, then top with fresh strawberries.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows. Place mixture in serving bowl and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: taco snack mix
directions: In large bowl, combine everything but margarine.
Drizzle melted margarine; toss to coat well.
Store in airtight container.

title: milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend to desired consistency, using low speed.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut up and remove all skin from chicken.
Brown in broiler with sprinkling of salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Combine all other ingredients in Teflon pan and mix well.
Add browned chicken and cook for 40 to 45 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Grind cookies; press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer nuts, chips and coconut.
Drizzle with milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: vanilla souffle
directions: Butter bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole and sift confectioners sugar over it.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in flour until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat. Add milk, stirring until blended.
Return to heat and bring to boiling and cook, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool. Beat egg yolks, sugar and extract together until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Stirring vigorously, pour sauce slowly into egg yolk mixture.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg whites until rounded peaks are formed.
Spread egg yolk mixture over egg whites and carefully fold together.
Turn into casserole set in boiling water bath.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately with berry puree if desired.

title: no-sag meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons cold water; stir to mix well, then while stirring, add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, beat egg whites until thick.
Gradually add sugar, a pinch of salt and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Turn mixer to low and fold in cornstarch mixture; when mixed, turn speed to high and beat until it stands in peaks.
Spread meringue over pie; be sure your meringue touches your crust all the way around.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
(This meringue will not sag, nor will it shrink.
It's also easy to cut.)

title: caramel pie
directions: Remove labels and cover cans with water.
Boil on high for 3 hours, adding hot water as needed.
Open carefully and pour in crust.
Top with whipped cream or leave plain.

title: mom's chicken soup
directions: Rinse chicken and remove most of fat.
(Too much fat will make soup greasy.)
Place in 6-quart pot and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil and skim scum as it rises.
Add onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 hours, then add carrot, rice, barley and bouillon.
Simmer soup one more hour.
Remove meat from bones.
Return meat to soup and discard bones.
Ready to serve.
Be careful of small bones.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, using juices from pineapple and strawberries as part of water (cold).
Add pineapple, strawberries and pecans. Let chill.

title: skokie casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until 3/4 done and drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain well.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix yeast, water, salt, sugar, oil, egg and 6 cups flour; mix well.
Add 4 more cups flour; mix quickly.
Knead on floured surface; let rise in greased bowl an hour, or until double in size.
Make into rolls and place on greased baking sheets.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.
Brush with butter and serve.

title: chocolate bonbon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add chocolate and nuts and blend.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
Serve plain or top with confectioners icing.

title: punch
directions: This recipe can serve up to 60 but if you'd like to serve 30, then use 1/4 gallon sherbet and 1/4 gallon ice cream, pouring in 1/2 bottle of ginger ale and 1/2 bottle of 7-Up, mixing well.
Add more ale and 7-Up as needed.
Very good!!

title: dreams delight
directions: Blend well; spread on top of crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cut together first three ingredients as for pie crust; put into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix together last five ingredients; pour into crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cherry cheese ball
directions: Mix and form in ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nanna's party cookie
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture. Stir in one cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining candies for decorating.

title: chocolate pound cake 2
directions: Mix butter, Crisco and sugar.
Beat until light.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder, flavoring and milk.
Beat real well.
Put into tube pan and cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix with whip.
Chill overnight.
Serve in round pumpernickel bread loaf.

title: creamy cashew chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the chicken, celery, green pepper and pimentos; set aside.
In a blender, combine all the other ingredients, except the cashews and lettuce.
Pour the blended ingredients over the chicken mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in uncooked pastry shell at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix the cornmeal, baking powder, salt and flour.
Then add milk and mix.
Add	eggs
and
oil	and
stir.
Pour
onto bottom of Dutch oven and bake for 25 minutes at medium-high.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cool.
Chop in pieces.
Add soup, onion and celery.
Add 3/4 of can of noodles.
One-half cup of broth can be added if necessary.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Put the rest of the noodles on top of casserole and bake another 5 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over crackers.
Seal in large bowl.
Continue to shake well for a day or two.

title: meat loaf with prosciutto and cheese(serves 6)
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Roll out on wax paper to about 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Cover to within 1-inch of edges with Prosciutto, then cheese, celery and onion.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix eggs and brown sugar; add butter and flour.
Blend well. Add chopped pecans.
Pour into pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while a little warm.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together and press into the bottom of a 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: easy french bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, except flour.
Gradually add flour until a soft dough (that no longer sticks to sides) forms. Knead 10 minutes, using flour as needed.
Probably will not use all the flour.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and wait 15 minutes, then form into 2 long loaves.
Brush with egg.
Let rise until doubled.
Meantime, preheat oven with a 9 x 13-inch pan of hot water on bottom shelf.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Reserve a little of the cheese. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs, Bisquick, milk, cheese and pepper in bowl for one minute.
Mix broccoli (or vegetable of your choice) and onion into bowl.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and cool. Mix cucumber, onion and carrot; drain. Add cottage cheese and salad dressing. Fold into gelatin. Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill until set.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine bran flakes and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add eggs and oil; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar, stirring only until combined. Portion batter evenly into greased 12 cup muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: rabbit and rice(microwave)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, combine rice, soup, water, diced onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Place cut pieces of rabbit on rice mixture.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with chopped chives and paprika.
Cover and cook on High for 30 to 35 minutes. Check rabbit for doneness.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: greenbrier salad
directions: Combine water, Jell-O and marshmallows and heat until marshmallows are dissolved.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and chill overnight in 6 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients together in a large bowl and mix with your hands (clean, of course) until well mixed.
Shape into a round loaf.
(This can make two.)
Put slices of bacon on the bottom of the baking pan.
Lay meat loaf on top of bacon and put a slice or two of bacon on top of the loaf.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: egg drop soup
directions: After the broth comes to a good boil, break eggs one at a time into the broth while stirring with a wire whisk.
Add diced onions with stems and parsley for color.
Don't cook more than 1 minute after adding the onion.
Serves 4.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Trim steak and slice across the grain into thin strips. Heat oil in a skillet and stir-fry the beef over high heat, stirring constantly until cooked, 3 to 5 minutes. Reduce heat and add carrots, celery, onion, soy sauce, garlic powder and pepper. Cover and cook until carrots are slightly tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Add zucchini and cook until tender-crisp, 3 to 4 minutes. Mix cornstarch and water until smooth. Add slowly to beef mixture, stirring constantly. Cook until thickened. Serve over hot rice.

title: corn chowder
directions: Drain the 2 cans of whole kernel corn and add the corn juice to potatoes and onions.
Add water and salt.
Cook until tender about 10 or 15 minutes.
Add whole kernel corn.
Bring back to boil.
Add cream-style corn, evaporated milk, pepper and cream. Then add butter.
Let cool.
Is much better after it sets.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Combine tomato, cucumber, onion and basil.
Mix.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over tomato mixture. Chill.
Toss lightly before serving.
Serve with additional picante sauce.

title: chocolate-cream bagel spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and white chocolate into a small bowl. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine well.
Store in airtight container.
Stir 1/3 cup of mix in 1 cup hot water.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and onion until they are transparent but not done.
Drain.
In a large bowl, mix sour cream, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over potatoes and bake 40 to 45 minutes (or until potatoes are tender).

title: chicken spaghetti bake
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Save stock and remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces and set aside.
Break spaghetti into short lengths and cook according to directions on package.
Drain and blanch spaghetti; set aside.
Place margarine in a large saucepan.
Add onion and celery.
Cook over low heat for a few minutes or until onion and celery is soft.
Add chicken stock and simmer 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup, a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Then add grated cheese, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add spaghetti to this mixture and let stand for 1 hour.
Add chicken to spaghetti mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: dominican republic arroz con leche (milk and rice custard)
directions: Mix rice with water and let stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Drain and discard water.

title: orange marmalade
directions: Peel fruit.
Run through food chopper.
Measure ground fruit and for each cup, add 1 1/2 cups water.
Boil 45 minutes.
Add pineapple and measure again.
For each cup, add 1 cup of sugar. Boil 30 minutes or until thick enough.

title: savory meat loaf and roasted potatoes
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, 1/2 can onions, egg and Worcestershire sauce thoroughly.
In a baking pan, shape firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Place potatoes around meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir potatoes.

title: tostadas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil; drain on paper towels.
Layer refried beans on tortillas, then add meat, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.

title: one pan spaghetti
directions: Bring to boil, then add 8 ounces spaghetti, uncooked.
Simmer until spaghetti is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried cakes
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with donut cutter; let rest 15 minutes.
Put into hot oil (365° to 375°).
Turn when light brown.

title: heavenly dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line with paper or grease 12 muffin cups.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add sugar and peanut butter and mix well. Gradually add milk. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Sprinkle with peanuts. Chill over night.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine the mashed yams, granulated sugar, eggs, salt and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Add to milk and vanilla and mix well.
Spoon into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: savory pork
directions: Saute meat in oil in a 10-inch skillet for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Add onion.
Saute 2 to 3 more minutes.
Drain apricots.
Add syrup and barbecue sauce to pork.
Add salt and black pepper.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green pepper.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Stir in mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add apricots and pineapple; heat gently.
Serve over rice or parsley noodles.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, half of the margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir well. Spoon into greased casserole dish. Stir rest of margarine into corn flakes. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: bran flax muffins
directions: Mix together flour, flax seed, bran, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Stir in carrots, apples, raisins and nuts. Get combined milk, beaten eggs and vanilla. Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients. Stir until moistened; do not overmix. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 15 medium-size muffins.

title: tabouli
directions: Wash parsley and drain.
Soak crushed wheat in a large salad bowl with water for about 3 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Remove stems from parsley and chop very fine.
Add to wheat with other ingredients.

title: lazy daisy sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and flour sifted with baking powder.
Scald milk and butter.
Beat into batter and thoroughly mix.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: watermelon fruit bowl
directions: Combine fruit and marshmallows; fill watermelon shell. Garnish with additional marshmallows; chill.
Serve with Mandarin Dressing.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Place in bowl and beat until well mixed.
Place in lightly greased floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it springs back with touch of finger.
Good frosted with cream cheese frosting.

title: pear butter
directions: Grind all fruits.
Add SureJel.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly.
Add sugar and bring to rolling boil.
Boil 20 minutes, skim, pour into jelly jars and seal.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat, blend in flour and add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Add cheese. Season with salt and pepper and continue to cook until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Spread half in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Arrange potatoes and onion slices over cheese.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake one hour in an oven preheated at 350°.
Yields 8 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Put in bowl in order given; beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: brisket
directions: Trim as much fat from brisket as possible.
Place 1/2 of sliced onion rings into a large roaster.
Put brisket into roaster and top with remaining onions.
Pour bottle of liquid smoke over brisket.
Cover closely; bake at 325° for 6 to 8 hours (overnight).
Let sit for 1 to 2 hours, then remove from juice. Discard onions and juice.
Slice thinly and serve with barbecue sauce.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Mix the next 4 dry ingredients and raisins.
Combine together the wet and dry ingredients.
Take the chilled butter; with 2 table knives, cut together until totally mixed.
Do not mix too much, but until a lump consistency.
Form into a round stone shapes about 2 inches thick.
Place on a baking sheet in oven preheated to 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until a golden brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add salt.
Bring next 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Sugar Twin.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour dressing over vegetables. Let stand 1 hour.
Mix 3 to 4 times. Drain thoroughly.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water (salted) until tender for 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a large bowl, beat butter, sugars until creamy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.

title: toll house cookie on a variation
directions: Follow recipe on Nestle chocolate chip bag, except completely melt butter (don't just soften).
Add the oatmeal, Grape-Nuts and chips to final mixture.
Preheat oven to 350° (not 375°).
Bake for 10 to 11 minutes, taking out while not yet warm.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in crock-pot; add cooked hamburger and Manwich. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: squash-onion casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon and grated cheese over top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: meatless whole wheat lasagna
directions: Total precooking time is approximately 1 hour.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots (about a package).
Melt butter; stir in flour. Add the milk and let thicken.
Add cheese, salt and pepper; stir until melted.
Put carrots in casserole dish.
Pour white sauce over carrots.
Sprinkle onions on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until onions are crispy.

title: peanut brittle i
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil until clear.
Add peanuts. Stir with wooden spoon using medium heat.
Cook until pink syrup turns brown.
Peanuts should be brown also.
Syrup will be a little thick and makes a hard string.
Quickly mix in soda, butter, and salt; pour on a lightly buttered foil covered tray. Let cool and break into pieces.

title: orange-nut bread
directions: Extract juice from the orange; strain and add boiling water to make 1 cup.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cheesy potato chowder
directions: Coat Dutch oven with vegetable cooking spray; use medium-high heat.
Add sliced onions and red pepper; saute until tender. Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water; stir until smooth.
Stir in remaining 3 3/4 cups water.
Add cornstarch mixture to pan.
Stir in potatoes, bouillon granules, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add corn; cook additional 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Ladle into bowls.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley.
Yields 7 cups (167 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion 5 minutes; drain.
Combine with soup, sour cream and carrot.
Mix stuffing mix and butter together. Layer half of stuffing mix on bottom of pan, then add squash mixture.
Top with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken marsala
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Add mushroom soup, Marsala wine, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium for about 15 minutes until chicken is done.
Serve with noodles.

title: mountain applesauce cake
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Stir good.
Mix flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, baking soda, nuts and raisins together in separate bowl.
Pour mixture of bowl #1 into bowl #2 and mix together by hand.
Pour into tube pan and bake.
Bake at 250° for about 3 hours.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Wash and thoroughly crush fully ripe blueberries.
Measure 4 cups; add lemon juice.
Measure sugar and set aside.
Place berries in a large, flat bottomed kettle.
Add pectin and stir until dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil, add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Bring to a full rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, skim with a metal spoon and pour into sterilized jars to within 1/4 inch of top.
Seal with new lids and process in a water bath canner at simmer temperature for 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 half pints.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well. Store in tightly covered container.
To serve, put 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix in cup.
Fill 3/4 full with boiling water.
Yields 25 to 36 cups from this mix.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Grease 8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Core cauliflower.
Place 1 cup of small flowerets in boiling, salted water to which 2 tablespoons lemon juice has been added. Cook about 5 minutes; drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soups and peppers. Set aside. Brown meat and onions; drain. Add refried beans and taco seasoning to meat. In bowl, mix cheeses together. In 9 x 13 pan, put 1/2 of sour cream mixture in bottom. Fill warm tortillas with meat and cheese. Roll and place in pan. Add remaining sour cream mixture on top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Cut cucumber in half lengthwise, scoop out seed and discard. Grate the cucumber and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients with cucumber; chill thoroughly.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups sauce. Delicious over salmon loaf or fish.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Cook
bacon in large skillet until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
In same skillet, brown ground beef and onion until beef is thoroughly cooked. Drain.
In 3 1/2 to 4 quart slow cooker, combine cooked bacon, cooked ground beef and onion and all remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 8 hours.
Serves 6.

title: sausage-brown rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown and drain.
Stir in rice, milk, celery, green pepper, onion, soup and mushrooms.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook uncovered in a 350° oven until center is bubbly.
About 45 minutes.

title: caribbean flan
directions: In blender, mix evaporated milk, condensed milk, 4 whole eggs, 2 yolks and vanilla.
Blend.
Take sugar and caramelize (in mold) in oven at 350° until golden brown.
Cover all sides of mold with sugar.
Pour mixture into mold.
Bake in oven at 350° in bain-marie for 1 hour until firm.
To remove, replace bain-marie with cool water.
Let set until warm, then flip onto dish and refrigerate.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Melt cream cheese and soup in double boiler.
Dissolve gelatin in warm water.
Stir gelatin into cheese and soup mixture.
Stir in onions and celery.
Add mayonnaise. Stir in shrimp and pour into mold lightly greased with the mayonnaise.
Chill overnight.

title: lazy beef casserole
directions: Put meat in a casserole with the wine, consomme, pepper, rosemary and onion.
Mix flour and bread crumbs; stir into the liquid.
Cover and bake at 300° for about 3 hours (or a lower temperature and longer cooking time may be used if it is more convenient).
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in ungreased casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread dough.

In a small bowl, combine egg yolks, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic powder, oregano, pepper and olive oil. Roll out bread dough to an approximate 10 x 14-inch rectangle (dough should be about 1/8-inch thick).
Spread egg yolk mixture over surface.

title: sweet potato pie - best yet!
directions: Cook in pie
shell
until almost done at 350°.
Now add Topping on top of pie.

title: deviled egg variations
directions: Mix into mashed yolks.
Spoon into egg white halves.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon caviar on each egg.

title: three bean meal
directions: Brown meat then add beans and tomatoes.
Simmer until hot. Serve with crackers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Drain artichokes; chop and save juice. In a shaker jar, mix reserved juice, oil, vinegar, mustard, garlic and basil; shake well.
Mix in pasta.
Add all the rest of the ingredients (add oil to taste).

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasoning.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
In an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish, layer half the noodles, then half the meat sauce, then half the Mozzarella cheese, then half the Velveeta and half the Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buckeyes
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Blend first three ingredients very well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown onion in oleo; add green chilies with soup and chicken broth.
Cut tortillas in bite sizes.
In a greased casserole, put layers of tortillas, chicken, cheese and soup mixture; repeat. Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: sunny day soup
directions: Peel, seed and section Florida oranges.
Put in blender. Blend, then pour into bowl.
Next, place bananas, pineapple with juice and cherries in blender.
Blend and mix well with oranges. Add sugar and stir into mixture.
Pour into soup dishes and sprinkle with coconut.
Serve chilled.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sweet potato snowballs
directions: Cut an elephant (medium size) into small bite-size pieces. (This usually takes about 2 months.)
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over gas fire in an open pot for about 4 weeks, maintaining 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, two rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary...most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: white trash
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave.
Follow directions on package. Mix dry ingredients in a large container.
Pour melted almond bark over dry mix.
Stir to coat everything.
Turn out on wax paper to cool.
Break apart when cooled.
Store in airtight container. Makes good gifts.

title: grandma ziegler's chicken 'n dressing
directions: Break bread into small pieces and brown in toaster for just a few minutes.
Add eggs, onion, salt, pepper and broth.
(May want to add a little at a time.)
Add chicken (off the bone) and continue mixing by adding broth until the mixture is completely mixed and juicy.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Add boiling water to make spread.
Bake at 350° for not more than 3/4 hour.

title: italian frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon butter until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in tomato; set aside.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in pan sprayed with Pam. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix well and spread over chicken.
