Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Baste chicken and bake 30 more minutes.

title: darn goods
directions: Heat fat or oil (1 1/2 inches) to 375° in electric skillet. Mix sugar and cinnamon in paper or plastic bag; set aside.
Stir baking mix and water to a soft dough.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.
Fry about 1/2 minute on each side or until golden brown and puffy.
Drain.
While warm, shake puffs in sugar mixture in bag.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in shortening (pour off fat). Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar,
syrup
and butter.	Add eggs, flavoring and pecans.
Pour
in
uncooked
pie
shell and cook 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes or until firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Mix 1 egg and 3 egg yolks.
Save whites for topping.
Stir in milk. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Put small amount of custard in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Add 1/3 custard for each layer.
Makes 3 layers and end with custard.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and 2 packages of strawberries.
Add pineapple (not drained) and bananas.
Cool until syrupy.
Put half in pan and set in refrigerator.
When set, spread with sour cream and rest of the jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Put the sugar in an aluminum or enamel pan (not Teflon).
Add water and stir; bring to boil.
Reduce heat so that mixture boils, but not furiously.
Stir constantly until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add shelled nuts, stirring gently.
Stir until evaporation reduces the liquid to zero and nuts crust. Sprinkle vanilla over nuts.
Stir until pan is dry and nuts are dry.
Spread nuts on cold cookie sheet (I put down wax paper) and let cool before packaging.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Mix potatoes, water, celery, carrots, onions, parsley, bouillon cube, salt and pepper in cooking pot and simmer 20 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Do not mix above ingredients.
Put each ingredient in separate layers in 13 x 9 inch pan.
Press each layer down as you would in making pie shell.
Finish top layer by spreading condensed milk over it.
Line cooking pan with greased wax paper and bake for
25 minutes at 350°.
When cookies are done, peel off wax paper, cut cookies and cool.

title: shrimp-crab au gratin
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onions in butter.
Mix flour and butter and microwave 1 minute.
Add milk and microwave 5 minutes. Whisk until smooth and thick white sauce.
Mix together all ingredients and pour into casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly throughout.

title: monterey bread
directions: Mix together.
Split loaf of French bread lengthwise.
Form cover for bread with aluminum foil.
Spread mixture on the two halves.
Put in broiler for a couple minutes.
Watch closely; it burns easily.
Serves 10.

title: rolls
directions: Combine milk, Crisco and sugar.
Bring to boil, then cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water, add beaten egg and yeast.
Sift flour with salt.
Add liquid to flour and salt. Turn to floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, covered, and let rise until double in size.
Knead again, then make into rolls. Let rise again then bake.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler or microwave oven.
Combine tomatoes and green chillies with cheese and sausage.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat sugar, oleo, flour and eggs.
Add pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown chops on both sides in oleo.
Remove from pan.
Pour water in pan and add bouillon.
Stir until dissolved.
Add rice and seasonings.
Pour all into an ovenproof casserole.
Place chops on top of rice.
Top each chop with a slice of onion, tomato and green pepper.
Cover and cook until done, about 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Makes 4 servings.

title: viola's pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat in flour and flavoring.
Pour into tube pan (greased and floured) and bake at 300° for one hour and at 325° for 15 minutes. Do not open oven until cake is done!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen corn
directions: Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Cook and package.

title: creamy fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream. Mix until well blended. Serve fresh fruit and cookies as dippers. Makes 2 cups.

title: corn bread or muffins
directions: Mix together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add the remaining ingredients to the mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: kraut-pork pinwheels(from 1975 edition)
directions: Combine pork, crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
On a piece of waxed paper, pat meat mixture to a 10 x 7-inch rectangle.
Combine the sauerkraut and onion; spread evenly over the meat.
Starting with the narrow side, roll up the meat in a jelly roll fashion.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Arrange bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: black and white and good-all over
directions: Remove paper from half of the ice cream sandwiches and fit into bottom of a rectangular baking dish.
Mix Cool Whip and rum flavoring.
Cover with half of the Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat layering.
Freeze overnight.
To serve, cut in 1/2 sandwich size squares.
Garnish each serving with whatever you like, such as chocolate curls, nuts, mint leaves, sliced almonds, mandarin orange slices and cherries with stems.

title: bun bars
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture over bottom of 15 x 10-inch pan.
(Anything smaller than 15 x 10-inch won't hold it.)

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream one-third sugar with butter and salt in a large bowl. Blend extract, 2 tablespoons milk and remaining sugar into mixture.
Gradually stir remaining milk into frosting until desire spreading consistency is reached.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Blend in eggs, water and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Enclose a mint wafer in about 1 tablespoon of chilled dough.
Place on baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Top each with a walnut half.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs together until lemon colored.
Beat sugar in, then add butter, salt, syrup and pecans.
Cook in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken
directions: Combine cheeses with the 4 cooked, crisp, crumbled bacon.
Put in a bowl.
Add eggs as the binding agent.
Season with salt.
Use a scoop or roll into 8 balls with your hands.
Fill each chicken breast with the cheese, bacon and egg mixture.
Wrap 1 strip of uncooked bacon around each filled chicken breast.
Bake on a broiler pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma lela biscuits
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Pour mix into bowl and add 1/4 c. oil and 3/4 c. milk.
Add self rising flour until you can roll dough onto floured board.
Cut out biscuits, and place on pan.
Bake at 350 degrees, until done.

title: cinnamon applesauce cake
directions: In saucepan, dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Heat until dissolved.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add applesauce and lemon juice.
Fills 8 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put yeast in 7/8 cup cold water to dissolve.
Set aside.
Place butter, sugar and salt in large bowl. Add remaining water and stir until butter melts.
Let cool, then stir in yeast.
Add flour a little at a time.
Beat egg and add. Stir into mixture well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Take out and make 2 hours before cooking.
Bake at 450°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli, bacon and onion in bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add to broccoli.
Add cashews before serving.

title: joyce's strawberry salad
directions: Mix
pretzels,
melted oleo and sugar together.
Pat in greased 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Bake
minutes
Cool. Dissolve
jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and chill until thickened.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put on top of cooled crust.
Put strawberry mixture on top and chill.

title: crisp okra patties
directions: Place okra in pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix well, then put enough flour over okra to coat well all slices. Add enough cold water to cause okra to form batter thick enough to cling together. Drop by tablespoon into deep, sizzling hot grease. Turn once and cook until patty is golden brown on both sides.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
In top of a double boiler, beat egg yolks slightly.
Add the reserved pineapple syrup, the sugar, vinegar, butter or margarine and dash of salt.
Place over hot water.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens slightly and barely coats a spoon, about 12 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine fruits and marshmallows.
Pour custard over and mix gently.
Whip the cream; fold into fruit mixture.
Turn into serving bowl.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Garnish with fresh orange sections and mint leaves. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: simple low-fat tuxedo pasta
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain and keep warm. Meanwhile in a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add chicken and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes until golden brown. Add zucchini and pepper. Cook 3 more minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add water and lemon juice. Simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1 tablespoon of butter. Add pasta and 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese. Toss to mix.
Serve on plate or platter. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: ambrosia fruit dip(sugar free, low-fat)
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Carve balls from your favorite melon to accompany dip.
This dip can also be served as a topping for any fruit salad.
Makes 2 cups or 8 servings. Four tablespoons per serving.
Diabetic exchange:
1/2 nonfat milk, 1 1/2 fat.

title: lynn's muscadine pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash fruit; separate skins from pulp and seeds.
Set skins aside; cook pulp about 10 minutes in a boiler; strain.
Add sugar to juice and bring to a boil.
Add skins and cook about 30 minutes.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Pour mixture into a crust and top with a crust, slitting the top crust and crimping the edges.
Moisten the top crust with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut up into smaller pieces.
Set aside.
Mix together mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese in medium bowl. Add artichoke pieces and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt.
Then add milk.
Mix.
Makes two 8-inch pie crusts.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat together butter, eggs, sugar, sour cream, bananas and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O according to directions on packages.
Add rest of ingredients and put in molds to chill.

title: thai chicken salad
directions: Stir together dressing, sugar, peanut butter, soy and red pepper.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Brown sausage, drain off fat.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in dish.
Bake at 350° (preheated) for 35 to 40 minutes.
The cheese will rise to the top during baking.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peppered pecans(serves 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In small skillet, melt butter.
Add garlic, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Cook 1 minute.
Toss pecans with butter mixture; spread in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour or until pecans are crisp; stir occasionally.
Makes 3 cups.

title: pretend soup for kids
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in cereal bowls and then whisk.
Top with bananas and berries.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender on high until ice cubes are completely chopped and drink is thick and frothy.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 onion.
Pour into one quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix well in order given.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake 1 hour (at 350° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 300°).
Test as for custard pie (use silver knife).

title: no-bake pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, Cool Whip, instant pudding and spice together. Pour into cooled crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: potato kugel
directions: In small skillet, brown onions in fat.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine onions, potatoes, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spread mixture in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Kugel will be browned.
Serve hot.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Mash with a fork and add remaining ingredients.
Don't use blender because they may be watery.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt; add M&M's.
Bake at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Place on bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (ungreased).
Salt and pepper. Form hamburger into balls; place on potatoes.
Salt and pepper. Dice up one onion and spread on hamburger balls.
Pour vegetable soup and mushroom soup over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: potatoes served with chicken seasoning
directions: Put butter in pan.
Roll potatoes in dry ingredients.
Place potatoes in pan and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add Egg Beaters, 1/4 cup at a time. Sift 2 1/4 cups flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking powder together; add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Beat until well blended.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Arrange sliced apples on top.
Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and cinnamon.
Spread over apples; dot with additional margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until tests done.
Enjoy!!!

title: grilled pork tenderloin and pineapple
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Trim excess fat from tenderloins.
Place tenderloins in a large, shallow dish.
Pour marinade over tenderloins.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 24 hours, turning occasionally.

title: scallop stew(for 2)
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add scallops, cut in quarters.
Keep turning scallops as they cook until they lose the gray look.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
Place top of double boiler over lower part which has boiling water in it.
Add milk (warm).
Let stand until very hot.
Add paprika, if desired.

title: krispy indian corn
directions: You will need tan raffia.

title: pineapple cooler
directions: Mix the juices and frozen orange juice concentrate.
Chill. Add the soda immediately before serving.
Serve over ice in tall glasses with straws.
Super on hot days!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until firm and tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Chop and mix other ingredients with macaroni.
Chill overnight and serve with crackers.
Makes a complete meal.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix together the flour, soda and baking powder; add alternately with chocolate paste. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Cook at least 1/2 hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook garlic and onion in oil until soft.
Add beef and seasoning.
Cook until meat is brown.
Drain excess grease.
Add tomato paste and hot water.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend beaten eggs with Ricotta cheese in small bowl.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put a thin layer of meat sauce, half the noodles, all the Ricotta cheese mixture and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with half remaining meat sauce, rest of noodles, remainder of meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jellied fruit salad
directions: Mix jellos together and add boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple and blend well.
Let mixture chill until it begins to thicken.
Add the remaining ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Chill until firm.

title: layered nachos
directions: In a 13-inch dish, layer the ingredients as listed.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate-oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies, 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and
congeal
the first 4 ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread on top of congealed salad.

title: stromboli(pizza roll)
directions: Prepare hot roll mix as directed on package.
Roll dough into a thin large rectangle.
Mix together egg yolks, Parmesan cheese, parsley leaves, garlic powder, oregano, pepper and oil.
Spread this on dough, then top with your pizza favorites, pepperoni. etc., ending with the Mozzarella cheese.
Roll the dough and ingredients into a roll (like a jelly roll) and place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Brush dough with egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Slice and serve.
Warm spaghetti sauce and use as a garnish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli, onion and cheese in a baking dish, 8 x 12-inch.
Combine soup, milk, egg and mayonnaise.
Pour mixture over layers.
Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes; cook until partly done.
Drain.
Mix butter, soup and cheese.
Add to potatoes.
Place in casserole dish. Cover with 1/8 cup melted butter combined with cornflake crumbs. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise into eighths.
Line a shallow baking pan with foil and put all ingredients into the pan, tossing well to coat the potatoes with oil and seasonings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or at a higher temperature for less time if you wish.
Adjust seasoning if necessary.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake by directions on box.
Pour into a sheet pan and bake.
When cake is done, punch holes in the cake while still warm.
Make a sauce of milk, sugar and coconut.
Cook until sugar melts.
Pour over cake and let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain fruit juice; mix with orange juice, then add 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and add jellos.
Stir until dissolved. Cool and add fruit.
Chill.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with milk in double boiler or microwave (1 minute).
Stir in nuts.
Drop mixture on cookie sheet greased with oleo.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Melt paraffin with Hershey bars in double boiler.
Dip candy in chocolate with a toothpick, then use the toothpick to put a drop of chocolate in the hole left by the toothpick.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Beat the eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, flour, salt and evaporated milk.
Continue to beat until smooth and all sugar dissolved.
Add vanilla and pour into freezer can.
Add enough whole milk to fill freezer can to fill line.
Follow freezing directions of your particular freezer.
When frozen, remove dasher and re-pack, sealing can with foil or plastic wrap.
Cover can with alternate layers of ice and salt, and cover entire bucket with newspaper and cloths to insulate it well.
Allow to remain 1 to 4 hours.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole 1
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all other ingredients except cheese and margarine.
Add broccoli.
Cut margarine in small pieces and stick down in broccoli.
Spread cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mom's homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar. Let stand several minutes until yeast puffs.
In large bowl, pour 1 quart warm water, 1/2 cup sugar and salt; stir until dissolved. Add 4 cups of flour, stirring until mixed well.
Add yeast mixture at this time and continue to add flour, a cup at a time, until the dough can be handled without being sticky.
Sprinkle flour onto table surface and place dough on it.
Continue to knead the dough until it becomes stiff.
Approximately
8 to 10 cups of flour will be used in this recipe.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour over broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon.
Marinate 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coney islands
directions: Place chili in a 1 quart casserole dish.
Microwave 2 minutes on High or until hot and bubbly, stirring once.
Set aside.
Place hot dogs on open buns.
Arrange on paper plate.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on Power 8, or until hot dogs feel warm.
Spoon chili over hot dogs.
Sprinkle with raw onion.
Top with grated cheese. Microwave 30 seconds on High or until cheese melts.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: macaroni-mushroom bake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Pour into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes. Uncover and cook 10 more minutes.

title: mexican nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Chop tomatoes and cube cheese.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn crock-pot on high until cheese melts, then turn to low until ready to serve.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large glass mixing bowl.
Add milk; stir.
Add margarine and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in vanilla, mix well and serve hot or cold over ice cream or cake.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs, then add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into oblong pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pour marshmallow cream over hot cake.
Cool. Top with Icing for Mississippi Mud Cake.

title: white butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and egg.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Break dough off in small balls and roll them in white sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press down with glass or fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spray 8 1/2 x 11 x 2-inch casserole. Melt oleo and mix all other ingredients in a bowl and pour in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter 3-quart casserole dish.
Set aside.
Place bread in a medium bowl.
In a small saucepan, over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour over bread pieces. Toss.
Set aside.
Warm milk in medium saucepan over medium heat. Melt 6 tablespoons butter in a high-sided skillet over medium heat. When butter bubbles, add flour.
Cook, stirring 1 minute.
While whisking, add hot milk, a little at a time, to keep mixture smooth. Continue cooking, whisking constantly, until mixture bubbles and thickens, about 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove pan from heat; stir in salt, nutmeg, peppers, 3 cups Cheddar cheese and 1 1/2 cups Gruyere or 1 cup Pecorino Romano.
Set the cheese sauce aside.
Cover large pot of saltwater.
Bring to boil.
Cook macaroni until the outsides of pasta is cooked and the inside is underdone, 2 to 3 minutes. Drain macaroni; rinse under cold water.
Drain well.
Stir in cheese sauce.
Pour in prepared dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over.
Add bread crumb mixture over top of macaroni.
Bake until golden brown, 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: platter cookies
directions: Mix and drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 360° for 15 minutes.
These spread to a large cookie.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Place all ingredients in a large pot. Add water to cover.
Simmer for 12 hours, or until beans are tender.
Stir beans about once each hour and add water if necessary while simmering.
Near end of cooking period, a pound a smoked sausage links may be added.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.
Freezes well.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Saute onion in melted butter.
Peel potatoes and cut in small cubes (or use 1 package hash browns).
Add to onions and barely cover with hot water.
Season with garlic salt, salt and pepper. Cook until mushy.
Stir in 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Cut cheese into thin slices and stir in.
Stir until cheese is melted. Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 soup cans of milk, depending on how thick you prefer soup.
Correct seasoning.
This is good cold or hot.
It can be made a day or two before serving.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Cut one pkg. of rolls into quarters and put in the bottom of a greased Bundt Pan.
In a small bowl, add sugar, and cinnamon and mix.
Take 1/3 of the sugar mixture and spread over the rolls in the Bundt Pan.
Do the same with the other 2 pkg. of rolls.
You should have 3 layers when you are done.
In a sauce pot, melt the butter and add the vanilla and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil. Pour over the mixture in the Bundt Pan.
Put into a 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes; cool.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and raisin mixture.

title: s. f. italian cold remedy
directions: Mix together, have one or more, go to bed and sweat your cold out!

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in heavy skillet.
Cook slowly; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove the candy from heat while testing.
Add nuts and salt to mixture.
Cook to hard crack stage (290°), stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda; stir to blend.
Mixture will bubble.
Pour onto greased platters.
Cool partially by lifting around edges with spatula.
Keep spatula moving under mixture so it won't stick.
When firm but still warm, turn over. Break in pieces when cold.

title: overnight layered green salad
directions: Shred lettuce into shallow serving dish. Top with onions, chestnuts, celery and peas in that order. Then add mayonnaise. Sprinkle on sugar, cheese, salt and garlic powder. Cover and chill in the refrigerator. Before serving, sprinkle on the eggs and crumbled bacon. Arrange tomatoes on top.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together. Whip cream and fold in carefully.
Pour into pastry shell; spread evenly.
Cover with prepared cherry pie filling.
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll a teaspoonful of cheese mixture into a ball; press with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: dee's dip
directions: Mix together (well).
Store in covered Tupperware bowl in refrigerator.
Will keep several days.
Good with raw vegetables, chips and crackers.

title: walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and place in shallow greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter or margarine.
Blend in flour and instant chicken bouillon.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Blend in milk.
Cook until thick.
Pour over broccoli.
Heat water plus 6 tablespoons butter or margarine together and pour over stuffing.
Stir in nuts.
Top broccoli with this mixture and bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until heated through and stuffing begins to brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: kugelis(lithuanian potato pudding)
directions: Chop onion and dice bacon.
Saute until golden.
Peel and grate potatoes.
Drain off liquid.
Pour scalded milk over potatoes.
Add pepper, salt, onion, bacon and egg yolks.
Mix well. Stiffly beat egg whites and fold into the mixture.
Pour into well-greased roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. When done, slice into oblong pieces.
Serve with sauteed chopped bacon and onions, sour cream or both.

title: casserole made with kraft macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Cook macaroni and drain. Stir in green pepper, mustard and 1/2 can of cheese sauce.
Spread on bottom of 12 x 7 1/2-inch pan.
Top with meat mixture.
Dot with remaining cheese sauce.
Sprinkle garlic croutons on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: extremely moist fruit cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add remaining in order listed and beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine
first	7 ingredients;	pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish or larger.
Combine corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter
and
sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10, but I served at least 20.

title: lazy coconut custard pie
directions: Cook at 375° for 10 minutes and then reduce heat to 300°. Cook until custard is set and pie is golden brown.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, Seven-Up and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased, floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: ham puffs
directions: Combine ham, cheese, green pepper and onion.
Stir in milk, egg yolks and bread crumbs.
Fold in egg whites.
Fill 6 greased 6 ounce custard cups.
Bake in pan of hot water at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.
Turn out on plates.
Top with mushroom sauce.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet rice
directions: Add the last 2 ingredients to the hot, cooked rice.
Mix and let stand for at least 5 minutes on very low heat before serving.

title: hillbilly caviar
directions: Mix all together. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix ingredients in
order
given.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan, greased and lined
with
wax paper in 275° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: presbyterian johnny cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix into the shortening, alternating with buttermilk.
Add dry cornmeal and mix.
Pour into an 8x8x2 greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot and enjoy

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease a round pizza pan.
Mash cookie dough around pizza pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 8 minutes or until a little overdone. Let cool.
Blend cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spread onto crust.
Arrange fruit on top of cream cheese and sugar mixture.

title: italian noodle casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Stir together the sausage, noodles and spaghetti sauce.
Spoon 1/2 the mixture into a buttered 14 x 22-inch casserole.
Spread the cottage cheese over this layer; cover with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wonderful warm weather watermelon sherbet
directions: Blend watermelon in the blender until juicy; pour through strainer to keep missed seeds out.
Blend in other ingredients and churn according to your churn instructions.
Makes a little over 1 quart.
(I triple the recipe to fill my 4-quart churn.)

title: peabody muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins well.
Sift four with sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl.
Add melted butter to milk and egg.
Beat to mix well.
Add vanilla.
Make a well in the center of flour mixture.
Pour milk mixture in all at once.
Stir with a fork, only until all ingredients are moistened. Do not beat or overmix.
Quickly spoon batter into muffin tins, filling each slightly more than half full.
Bake 15 minutes if using Gem muffin pans; 18 to 20 minutes for full size muffin pans. Remove from tins immediately.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients and marinate overnight or for several hours in the refrigerator.
Toss well just before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet and cook until browned.
Combine drained sausage.
Chill.
Shape mixture into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy stromboli
directions: Have all meats sliced thin at deli counter.

title: dill bread
directions: In 1/2 cup warm water, dissolve 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast; let set.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, eggs, cottage cheese and yeast mixture.
Mix; let rise until double.
Work down (knead a little).
Put into 2 bread pans (greased); let rise until doubled.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove; brush with melted butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: biscochitos
directions: Cream lard and sugar, add eggs, add sifted flour, baking powder, wine, anise, and vanilla.
Flour counter or cutting board before rolling out 1/4 inch thick; cut and dip into sugar blended with cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sidewalk chalk
directions: Mix together.
Put into waxed paper cups about 1/2-inch full. When it sets, peel off paper cups.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter medium size casserole dish. In a large bowl stir together sugar and flour.
Gradually stir in cheese.
Add drained pineapple and stir.
Pour ingredient into dish.
In another bowl combine cracker crumbs, butter and reserved juice.
Spread mixture on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Add all ingredients into punch bowl.

title: frosted date balls
directions: Blend all
together.
Roll
in
inch balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
While still warm, roll in additional powdered sugar.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an 8-inch square glass baking dish mix finely chopped artichokes with mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until heated through and top is light brown.
Makes 2 cups.

title: flan
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except sugar).
Brown granulated sugar in skillet until melted then pour into baking dish.
Pour all mixed ingredients over the sugar mixture.
Place baking dish in a pan of water.
Bake at 350 degrees until knife inserted into center of mixture comes out clean.
When flan has cooled, turn dish upside down onto plate.
Slice.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Fold in apples.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop favorite
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Layer pork chops on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: clam sauce(salsa di vongole)
directions: Heat oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add garlic and parsley and cook over medium heat for one minute, stirring constantly.
Add clams, clam juice, salt, and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for two minutes. Remove from heat and add butter.
Stir until butter has dissolved and serve at once over hot, drained pasta.
Grated cheese is not usually served with this sauce, but if you like it, use it.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge
directions: Microwave chips and milk for 2 minutes.
Add flavoring.
Pour in a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan and cool to cut into squares.

title: prince of wales cake(dates from 1860's)
directions: Beat eggs very lightly and add butter.	Work until light.
Beat all together and gradually put in flour, containing baking powder and water.	Stir into the batter cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Cut citron into small pieces, seedless raisins.
Wash and dry currants.
Stir all into the batter and bake in a quicker oven than necessary for other cakes, covering the top to prevent burning.
Bake until done.

title: fudge topping for ice cream
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cocoa and milk until smooth.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 4 to 5 minutes, until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows, butter and vanilla until marshmallows are melted.
Serve warm over your favorite ice cream.
This is a YUM, YUM.

title: mounds bar cake
directions: Mix as directed.
Bake in 2 round layer pans.
Cool and split for 4 layers.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Chop spinach into salad size pieces, removing coarse stems. Cook bacon.
Add vinegar, sugar, bacon grease and pepper together. Garnish spinach with eggs.
Pour hot dressing over and serve immediately.

title: play dough
directions: Light oven.
Get out bowl, spoons and ingredients.
Grease the pan.
Crack nuts.
Remove 18 blocks and 7 autos from kitchen table. Measure 2 cups flour.
Remove Nick's hands from the flour.
Wash flour off him.
Measure 1 more cup flour to replace flour on the floor.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in a sifter.
Get dustpan and brush up pieces of bowl Ryan knocked on the floor.
Get another bowl.
Answer doorbell.
Return to the kitchen and remove Nick's hands from the bowl.
Wash Nick.
Get out egg.
Answer phone. Return.
Take out greased pan.
Remove pinch of salt from pan. Look for Ryan.
Get another pan and grease it.
Answer the phone. Return to the kitchen and find Ryan.
Remove his hands from the bowl.
Wash shortening from him.
Take up greased pan and find 1/4-inch of nut shells in it.
Head for Nick who flees, knocking bowl off table.
Wash kitchen floor, wash table and walls and wash the dishes.
Call the bakery!
Lie down!

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine lightly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Note: You may mix and bake in 1 bowl.
I use a 10-inch deep dish pie plate to cook this.

title: oyster stew
directions: Check oysters between fingers and thumb for shell particles. Melt margarine over medium heat and put oysters into hot margarine.
Cook until oysters begin to curl at edges.
Add all milks; cook until just before boiling.
Do not boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve immediately with Zestas.

title: date cake
directions: Boil for 3 minutes.
Broil 4-inches from unit for 2 minutes or until nuts are quite "brown."
Cool in pan.
Freezes beautifully.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix all ingredients, form into 2 rolls and refrigerate until firm.
Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple except for 4 tablespoons. Combine flour with 4 tablespoons pineapple juice. Add this to pineapple. Add sugar and cheese. Pour into greased casserole dish. Combine butter and crackers and use for topping. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Good served with ham.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Squeeze juice out of lemons into a small container; add Accent and oil.
Let these ingredients sit overnight.

title: vanilla "tea" cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown. Yields approximately 75 cookies.

title: pineapple refrigerator dessert
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add pineapple and nuts.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers to cover a large platter or pan. Spread 1/2 of the pineapple mixture over the wafers.
Repeat with another layer of wafers and remaining 1/2 of the pineapple mixture. Chill overnight in refrigerator. Top with whipped cream. Serves 12.

title: warren's clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients together adding clam juice until the desired consistency is reached.

title: bubbles for kids
directions: Put in jar and give children straws to blow bubbles.
Send them outside for bubbles of fun.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, softened oleo and pineapple.
Add coconut, eggs and vanilla; blend well and pour into two 8-inch pastry-line pie pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry-orange nutbread cups
directions: For more variety, try topping your English muffin with part skim Mozzarella cheese or low-fat cottage cheese, followed by a pineapple ring, spiced apple ring or other sliced fruit.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan, layer half the dry bread cubes.
Combine applesauce, the 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spread applesauce mixture over bread cubes.
Layer remaining bread cubes atop.
Dot with butter.

title: no-fat pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add water.
Mix well, then pour by spoonful in skillet sprayed well with nonstick spray. Turn when bubbles form, then turn and cook on other side.

title: spinach lasagne(7 grams of fat per serving)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, mix all ingredients, except sauce, noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Spread 1/4 of sauce in lasagne pan (9 x 13-inch); top with 1/3 of noodles.
Spoon on 1/3 of cheese mixture.
Repeat sauce, noodles and cheese mixture twice more.
End with sauce.
Sprinkle remaining 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese on top (I use a little Parmesan cheese).
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours (until noodles are tender).
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cheese cake
directions: *Use rest of crumbs for crust.
Make sure they are tight together.

title: oil and vinegar dressing(makes 1 cup)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shaker and shake well.
Use over green or vegetable salad.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and pour over rhubarb the sugar, salt, egg yolks, flour and milk.
Bake at 375° until done.
Put on meringue and brown at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour, then add warm water slowly so it will be smooth.
Add to the milk that is just starting to boil. Will be thick, but you can add a little extra milk if necessary. Serve with Hot Butter Biscuits.

title: harvard beets(5 servings)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in top of double boiler over low heat. Remove top of double boiler from heat.
Add cornstarch, sugar and salt; stir until smooth.
Add vinegar and tarragon vinegar slowly; stir to make a smooth paste.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Add sliced, cooked beets.
Cover and place over simmering water in bottom of double boiler and heat for about 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer.
Add chicken.
Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° or 350° to warm thoroughly and melt cheese.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Cut marshmallows into pieces and place in greased pan.
Melt peanut butter and chips in pan.
Pour over marshmallows. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into pieces and enjoy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in baking dish.
Cover with 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers mixed with 1 stick of oleo.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lo-cal dip
directions: Mix well; keep in refrigerator when not in use.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown butter, brown sugar and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in microwave or conventional oven until softened, approximately 10 minutes.
Be sure and use bowls for microwave or bowls that can be used in conventional oven. Mix soup, mayonnaise, margarine, eggs and cheese.
Pour over broccoli in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until light brown on top and firm.
Serves 12.

title: marinating sauce for barbecues
directions: Mix well. Marinate meat overnight. Grill.

title: egg souffle
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and cheese in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Place in refrigerator overnight (covered).
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Crumble bacon on top for last 1/2 hour.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Cut together cake mix and oleo.
Mix together the sour cream and egg.
Butter the pan and pat 2/3 of cake mix mixture in the bottom of the pan.
Then spread the apples on the cake mix, then pour the sour cream mixture over the apples.
In remaining cake mixture, add brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the top of the sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Mix together, make meatballs.
Fry in oil until light brown.

title: ham roll-ups(microwave)
directions: Microwave cream cheese in small bowl on High (100%) until softened, 15 to 20 seconds.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, green onion and mustard.
Spread cheese mixture on ham slices.
Roll ham from narrow end.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Secure with wooden pick.
Place on paper toweling on carousel or large dinner plate. Microwave at High (100%) for 1 to 2 minutes.
Rotate plate half a turn if not using carousel.
Yields 16 appetizers.

title: candies
directions: Melt butter, cocoa and milk. Mix together. Add powdered sugar; stir and dissolve. Put in greased pan and put in refrigerator. Cut in squares.

title: banana butterscotch pie
directions: Mix pudding, filling and milk together.
Fold in 1/2 cup lite Cool Whip.
Slice bananas.
Put in crust. Pour mix in on top of bananas.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.
Equals 1 Bread, 1 Fruit and 1/2 Milk.

title: banana treasure
directions: Peel bananas.
(If using large bananas, split lengthwise.) Melt butter or margarine in large skillet over low heat.
Add sugar and stir until melted.
Add bananas and saute just until tender, turning once, about 10 minutes.
In bowl, blend softened ice cream and rum.
Remove bananas.
Sprinkle brown sugar glaze over them.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
(Note:
Leave enough shredded cheese to sprinkle on top.)
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.
Can be served with chili beans and a tossed salad.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix the powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick softened margarine; beat for 15 minutes, until fluffy. Spread over crust.
Spread the bananas and crushed pineapple over the first 2 layers.
Top the layers with the Cool Whip, cherries and chopped nuts.

title: tomato salad
directions: Stir together.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: kielbasa(sauerkraut with polish sausage)
directions: Cut bacon into small bits; brown slowly in kettle.
Add onions.
Cook until golden.
Add sauerkraut and grate an apple into it.
Add brown sugar and water.
Cook slowly and then add sausages.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Add potato flakes to thicken.
Stir thoroughly and take off burner.
I like to cook mine a day or two before eating.
It think it tastes better, but it can be eaten right away.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix well.
Shape into patties and dip in more bread crumbs. Fry.

title: layered mint surprise
directions: Crush cookie wafers or crush pie shells.
Layer jelly roll pan 1/4 to 3/8-inch thickness with crumbs.
Spread softened ice cream over top of crumbs.
Sprinkle peppermint candy crumbs on top of ice cream layer.
Add green food coloring to Cool Whip and spread on top.
Use rest of chocolate crumbs for top layer.
Freeze until ready to eat.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Press half of crumb mixture in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with jam.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: four-pasta beef bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, cook the beef, green peppers, onions, and mushrooms over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Drain pasta and place in large bowl; stir in the beef mixture, two jars of spaghetti sauce, and eggs.
Transfer to 2 greased 13 in. x 9 in. x 2 in. baking dishes.
Top with remaining sauce; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°F for 25 - 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
2 casseroles (8 - 10 servings each).

title: potato casserole
directions: Grate the cooked potatoes.
Add all the other ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Will need large pie pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1 to 1 1/2 stick margarine. Pour over dry stuffing mix and line dish with 1/2 of this mixture.
Mix above ingredient and pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave cheese dip
directions: Melt processed cheese in with picante sauce; mix well.
When melted and mixed, add sour cream.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: spicy shrimp, snow peas and baby corn
directions: Combine shrimp, salt, sugar, chili sauce, garlic and fresh ginger.
Marinate 1/2 hour.
In a frying pan, bring broth to boil. Add snow peas, corn, onion and red peppers.
Stir-fry until peas are slightly done.
Remove to platter.
Bring liquid to boil.
Add shrimp; cook until done.
Thicken with cornstarch; stir in vegetables.
Season and serve hot.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Combine hamburger, onions and spices; set aside. Cut tops off squash and shave a little off bottom, enough so squash will stand up. Take insides out leaving about 1 to 1 1/2-inches. Place squash on a cookie sheet and stuff meat mixture into it. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until meat is done.

title: poteet strawberry shortcake
directions: Puree 1/2 cup strawberries; set aside.
Refrigerate remaining berries.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Separate eggs, placing whites in medium size bowl and yolks in cup.
In large bowl, with electric mixer, beat together 1 1/2 cups sugar, the shortening and almond extract until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat until mixture is well combined.

title: grilled chicken and pasta florentine
directions: Advance Preparation:
Wash the spinach thoroughly and cook it in the chicken broth until tender.
Drain the spinach in a colander.
Save the broth and use a spoon or rubber spatula to press out excess moisture.
When cool, chop the spinach and set aside.
Grill the chicken breast meat.
Cool and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with whisk or mixer.
Stir in 1/2 of cool whip.
Use large bowl, line bottom with wafers or crackers. Cover layer with layer of pudding and then thinly sliced bananas. Then repeat with last layer of pudding.
Cover with remainder of cool whip when ready to serve.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set 2-3 hours or over night.
Can use sugar free pudding, skim milk, and low fat cool whip and it tastes just as good.

title: pizzelles
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, salt, anise flavoring and anise seed, then add flour.
Place on a pizzelle griddle.

title: fried hard crabs
directions: Clean and wash hard crabs thoroughly.
For 1 dozen hard crabs, combine 2 cups flour, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl. Lightly press bony, inner shell, being careful not to break back shell.
Dust in flour mixture and fry in small amount of cooking oil until golden brown.

title: low calorie brownies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Combine milk, orange juice and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 13 X 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degree for 30-35 minutes.
When cool cut in to squares.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: mexican-zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil and sugar.
Add zucchini and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Bake at 325° in 2 greased loaf pans for 1 hour.

title: camper stew
directions: Brown ground beef in frypan.
Drain off fat.
Place layers of potatoes, carrots and onions on top of ground beef.
Salt and pepper each layer as desired.
Pour tomato sauce over ingredients. Cook approximately 45 minutes on medium heat.
This recipe can also be prepared in crock-pot or in individual packets of aluminum foil and cooked over a campfire.
Delicious!

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash to tender crisp, cool.
Cook onion in butter until transparent.
Combine tomato sauce and BBQ sauce.
Layer squash, onion and cheese in 7x11 baking dish - two layers. Pour sauce over top. Sprinkle top liberally with stuffing mix and Parmesan.

title: charlie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop and remove kernels.
In a heavy saucepan, mix and boil for 5 minutes oleo, brown sugar and syrup.
Remove from heat and add salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Stir well (will foam).
Pour over popped corn and mix well in a large pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour. Stir once or twice during the hour.

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl; add cold water to cover. Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels to nut size.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour melted butter over.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and cut in fat, mixture will be crumbly.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Mix and knead well.
Roll out on floured surface and cut in small squares.
Let stand several hours and cook in hot broth.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Make crust by combining graham cracker crumbs with melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar. Press crumbs onto bottom and about 2/3 of the way up the sides of an 8-inch spring-form pan. Bake 5 minutes and set aside.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch dish with margarine.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Then make layers of sliced potatoes, sifted flour, chopped onion, thin pats of margarine, strips of Velveeta cheese and salt and pepper.
Repeat until dish is full.
Then add 1 cup of milk.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir with fork until blended.
No need to grease or flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back from touch.
Cool in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar through sifter.

title: pretzel congealed salad
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Pour over pretzels evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes and then cool. Cream together and spread cheese, Cool Whip and sugar over the pretzels.

title: parmesan potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of glass baking dish. Sprinkle with some of the Parmesan cheese.
Peel the potatoes and slice thinly.
Melt the margarine in saucepan or microwave.
Mix in the remaining cheese.
Layer the potatoes and the cheese mixture in the pie dish.
Bake for 1 hour, or until the bottom is browned.
Flip onto a plate and serve while still warm.

title: scotch oatmeal bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Combine oats, sugar, salt, shortening, molasses and boiling water; cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water; stir until dissolved.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Add raisins and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth, 10 minutes.
Add rest of flour.
Let rise about 1 1/2 hours or until double in bulk.

title: fruit stack cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Spoon evenly into 4 greased and floured 9-inch pie pans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove onto wax paper and let cool.
Put applesauce, cooked apples or you can use jam or jelly between layers. Sprinkle top with sugar.

title: diabetic apple pie
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in apple juice. Combine with apples and spice. Simmer until thick. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with margarine. Cover with top crust and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put sliced potatoes and butter in bottom of casserole dish. Sprinkle with onion and pepper.
Empty soup, undiluted, over potatoes, onion and pepper and enough milk to cover bottom of dish.
Add about 1 tablespoon of butter to top.
Cover and cook about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until brown.
Combine with soup, milk, chicken or turkey and cooked noodles.
Top with cheese and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Don't overbake or it will get pasty.

title: glorified rice
directions: Whip cream.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and rice.
Mix lightly.
Chill for 3 or 4 hours.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients well (beat).
Pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Chill one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with soup, mayo and other ingredients.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large fry pan, saute ground beef, mushrooms and onions in hot oil until golden brown.
Add bouillon cubes, water, salt, catsup and mustard, simmer 15 minutes.
Combine flour with cold water.
Slowly stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat, stir in sour cream, heat, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: classic divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; set aside.
Mix sugar, syrup, water and salt in a
medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking over medium heat until syrup cracks when dropped into small amount of cold water.
Pour syrup slowly into egg whites, beating constantly, until all syrup mixture has been added to egg whites. Continue beating until the candy loses its shiny look.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased or foil-lined cookie sheet.
Red or green food coloring may be added for Christmas.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: punch by mama lois
directions: Take two heaping cups of patience,

title: wild rice and white bean salad
directions: Cook package wild rice in broth and water.
Add the frozen peas, white beans, onion and red pepper during last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Allow rice mixture to cool slightly.
Mix Italian dressing with lemon juice and Mrs. Dash's seasoning to taste and combine with rice mixture.
Serve on bed of crisp lettuce.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix together & refrigerate.
Serve with white tortilla chips.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Fold in all at one time strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put 1/2 of mixture into baking dish as first layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream evenly over firm Jell-O as second layer.
Spoon remaining mixture over sour cream as third layer.
Refrigerate.
(Sliced bananas won't turn dark if soaked in lemon or orange juice for several minutes.)

title: chicken and batter(heritage)
directions: Preheat oven.
Melt shortening in a 13 x 15-inch pan.
Place salted chicken pieces in pan.
Do not crowd.

title: tomato jam
directions: Blanch tomatoes and peel.
Cut tomatoes in half and remove seeds.
Chop until texture is fine.
Mix 1 part tomato with 3/4 part sugar.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: corn dogs
directions: Boil hot dogs in water until they are cooked.
Dry off hot dogs before dipping into batter.
Mix all the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat the egg, then combine it with the milk.
Add the milk to the dry ingredients, then mix well.
Dip the hot dogs in the batter.
Heat the oil to 375°.
Cook 1 minute in hot oil or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon suckers
directions: You will also need sucker sticks and molds or ice tray.

title: roast sandwich meat
directions: Cook meat 3 hours at 300°.
Remove fat and bones. Add remaining ingredients. Cook for 3 hours. Serve on bun.
Freezes well.

title: kringla
directions: Mix in order given.
Dough should be stiff enough not to be sticky.
Let rest for 30 minutes or so.
Roll out, print, cut and set on greased cookie sheet on which you have sprinkled anise seed. Leave in a cool place overnight to dry.
Cover lightly or not at all.
Bake in the a.m. at 350° until light brown.

title: pineapple coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and cinnamon; set aside.
Cream butter and 1 cup sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Alternate flour and baking powder with sour cream.
Top cake with first 3 ingredients before baking.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese, creaming until well blended. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Shape dough into 8 balls; wrap each in plastic wrap and chill at least 2 hours.
Roll each ball of dough into an 8-inch circle on a lightly floured surface; cut into 8 wedges.
Combine walnuts, sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon mixture over each wedge of dough.
Starting at wide edge of dough, roll up each wedge. Shape into a crescent.
Place point side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: honey wheat muffins
directions: Stir together flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk, honey, oil and lemon peel; add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Grease muffin cups or line with paper baking cups; fill 2/3 full.
Bake in a 375° oven about 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: pumpkin and chocolate squares
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs in a large bowl.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Divide the batter in half.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cocoa; add to about 1 cup mixture.
Blend in vanilla.
Spoon into greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread evenly and add the pumpkin pie filling and spice to remaining batter.
Spread on top of the chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool in pan. Frost with Chocolate Glaze.
Makes 16 brownies.
I double recipe.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg, and melted butter.
Dough will be stiff.
Press into greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs, and box of confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.	Cool and cut into squares.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: Saute hamburger and onion.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
On top, add beans, corn and chili peppers.
Cover with cheese.
Mix cornbread according to directions and spread over top.
Bake until golden brown.

title: nana's pumpkin pie("the best")
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Slowly add sugar and spices. Mix on low speed.
Add pumpkin and mix on low.
Add evaporated milk.
Mix on low speed.
Pour pumpkin into pie shells.
Place pies on cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then lower oven to 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
Keep a check on pies. Deep dish will take longer to bake.

title: beefy now and later
directions: Brown meat and onions together; drain.
Cook zucchini in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: chocolate raisin bran jumbo cookies
directions: Beat margarine until smooth.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add cocoa mix, egg substitute and vanilla, beating until well blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in cereal.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks; cool.
Yields 1 1/4 dozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender in broth.
Add 1 pint of half and half milk.
Add jar of Cheez Whiz.
Stir until cheese is dissolved.
Add butter or margarine.
Enjoy.

title: slovak khrusty
directions: Beat egg and egg yolks until very light.
Beat in sugar, cream, salt and rum.
Stir in flour.
Dough will be soft.
Knead on floured board until smooth.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes. Roll thin about 1/8-inch or thinner.
Use a small amount of dough at a time and keep rest covered (has a tendency to dry out).

title: yeast bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour hot milk over sugar and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1/2 cup flour and mix thoroughly.
Stir in softened yeast and half of remaining flour; beat thoroughly.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until just tender; drain and cool.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Add the carrots and let stand at least 12 hours before serving.
Serve cold.
Keeps in refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Place margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put in oven until melted.
Mix other ingredients together except fruit and pour over melted margarine.
Then pour fruit on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix by hand.
Pat onto a cookie sheet type pan until 1/2-inch thick.
Then pour Top Mixture over it.

title: danish puff pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour until particles are the size of peas.
(I use a food processor.) Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture and mix with a fork. Gather pastry to a ball.
Divide in 2 halves; pat each half into a rectangle 12 x 3-inches on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Drop spoonfuls the size of walnuts onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Roy's favorite.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, using 2 round pans or sheet pan.
Let cake cool.
Cut in half if sheet pan.
Crumble one of the cake halves in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix together pineapple, pecans and pie filling.
Layer half of mixture on cake crumbs. Prepare pudding and pour 1/2 over fruit.
Crumble other half of cake layer, remaining fruit, then remaining pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut.

title: champagne sherbet punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine pineapple juice and ReaLemon.
Just before serving, scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Add champagne. Stir gently.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Batter will be watery.
Grease 9-inch pie pan lightly.
Pour in pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: elizabeth's rice krispie candy
directions: Melt on low heat the butter and peanut butter.
Blend in sugar and Rice Krispies (if too moist, add sugar.
I never used a whole pound.)
Chill slightly and form small 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Dip 1/2 of each candy into melted chocolate morsels if desired.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and milk until lukewarm and add to yeast mixture.
Add egg to mixture and stir in flour.
Knead lightly on lightly floured board. Let rise about 1 hour and punch down and let rise about 10 minutes. Shape into rolls and let rise 1 hour and bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown at 400°.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water and butter together to a boiling point in an enamel pan.
Add
flour
all
at once and stir constantly with wooden spoon until
mixture
leaves sides of the pan and forms into a big ball
(about
minute).	Remove	from heat; cool thoroughly. Add unbeaten
eggs,
one
at
a
time.
Beat to a smooth paste after each egg is added.
Then beat mixture until smooth and velvety.
Drop
from a spoon on an ungreased baking sheet, forming a ball the size
of a small orange.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.
When
cool
fill
with
favorite filling: vanilla or chocolate
pudding, strawberries and cream.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour in shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: apple butter muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In separate bowl, combine egg, milk and oil; stir into flour mixture.
Place 1 tablespoon batter into muffin cups; spoon 1 teaspoon apple butter.
Fill cups 2/3 full with remaining batter.
Combine pecans and 2 tablespoons sugar; sprinkle atop batter.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients (onion and garlic extra fine).
In large skillet or Dutch oven, saute gizzards in margarine, add onion and garlic.
Add liver last, mashing so that it dissolves into gravy.
Add rice and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: almond shorts
directions: Follow directions for Baking Powder Biscuits (steps 1 to 6). Roll into oblong, 1/4 inch thick about 10 x 12-inch.
Spread with soft butter lightly.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Roll up tightly lengthwise.
Seal edges well.
Cut into 12 equal parts about 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick.
Place each in a muffin cup (cut side down).
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown (set timer).
Makes 12 cinnamon rolls.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place
lightly	toasted
bread	in bottom of a buttered baking pan
x
13-inch).
Spread
chopped, cooked ham and shredded cheese
over
the
toast.
Beat
eggs
in a bowl with milk, salt, spicy brown mustard, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Boil water and remove from stove.
Add dates and soda.
Let stand.
Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add date mixture and nuts.
Fill greased and floured pans half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: steamy bean casserole
directions: In frying pan, cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel. Add onion to pan; cook until tender.
Remove from grease.
Combine thoroughly in a bowl, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.

title: reuben brunch casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put bread crumbs on bottom. Coarsely shred corned beef.
Layer meat over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and pepper in bowl.
Pour over corned beef mixture.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to bake, put casserole covered in 350° oven for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne according to package directions.
Pour layers of sauce in bottom of 9 x 2 x 13-inch dish.
Put in 4 of the noodles. Put in all the spinach to which has been added 1 beaten egg, the cream and salt to taste.
Add another layer of sauce.
Put 3 noodles over this.
Add all the Ricotta cheese to which has been added 2 beaten eggs and salt to taste.
Add half the grated Mozzarella cheese.
Add another layer of sauce, the remaining noodles, the remainder of sauce and the remaining Mozzarella cheese.

title: sweet tangy spareribs
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Sprinkle meat with tenderizer and prick with fork.
Rub meat on both sides with salt and a touch of cayenne pepper.
Place ribs, meat side up in a foil-lined shallow pan, preferably on a rack so fat will drain away from meat.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove and pour off fat.
When cool, cut into serving size pieces, place in large bowl and pour sauce over ribs.
Marinate overnight or for several hours.
Place on foil-lined broiler pan or foil covered charcoal grill.
Cook slowly (300° to 350°) for 20 to 30 minutes.
Baste often and turn at least once.

title: caviar cream cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add mayo, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and hot sauce; beat well.
Spoon cream cheese mixture in shallow serving dish.
Top with caviar, eggs and parsley.
Serve spread with assorted crackers.
Yield: 24 to 30 appetizer servings.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Mix with other ingredients.
Cut ham in small pieces and add to mixture. Mix well and put in a large casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: nonfat yogurt
directions: Combine 1/3 cup nonfat milk with milk powder.
Pour into large saucepan, and add remaining milk, stirring thoroughly to combine. Heat mixture, over low heat, until temperature is 190°.
Use candy thermometer, put into mixture, to determine temperature.
Cover and reduce heat to 110°.
Leave thermometer in saucepan.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add package of taco seasoning mix and mix as directed on package.
Add can of refried beans to beef and put in casserole dish.
Mix together with wire whisk the sour cream and green taco sauce.
Spread over beef and bean mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix together sugar, baking powder, flour and milk.
Pour into Pyrex dish on top of margarine.
Pour peaches on top of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream while warm.

title: 30 minute chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil magarine, water and cocoa.
Mix together flour and sugar, then pour hot mix over them.
Mix well.
Add eggs, milk, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While still hot, cover cake with frosting.
Then cover with chopped nuts.

title: chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt sugar and butter in large saucepan. Add 1 egg and then 1/2 flour, another egg and then remaining flour. Add chopped pecans and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch metal pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Yields 16 to 20 chewies.

title: my friend emma's cranberry orange relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges together.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix soup with sour cream; blend well.
Add mayo, spinach and chestnuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: waist-away rice pudding
directions: Scald milk; add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Add rice, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into a casserole and bake in slow oven (250°) about 45 minutes.
Stir during cooking.
Chill before serving.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; whisk in flour and garlic powder.
Cook, whisking constantly, 1 minute. Gradually whisk in milk; cook over medium heat, whisking until thickened. Add cheeses; cook over low heat, stirring until melted.
Stir in corn and ham.
Pour into a greased 2 quart baking dish.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except the eggs. Simmer over low heat, uncovered, until the onions are tender, about 10 minutes.
Arrange the eggs in two 1-quart jars with tightly fitted lids.
Pour 1 cup of vinegar mixture over the eggs in each jar.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Eggs may be stored in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough; spread spaghetti sauce in middle of dough (not too heavy).
Put on onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Layer meats and cheeses.
Fold dough from one side to top, then other side over that.
Pinch ends shut.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 2.

title: gonme's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in flour.
Add pecans.
Bake in buttered 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch or 11 x 7 1/2-inch pan for about 1/2 hour.
Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: apricot-nut balls
directions: Mix the apricots, coconut, nuts and milk.
Shape the mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Let candies stand until firm (about 2 hours).

title: gravy
directions: Add your choice of seasonings, reducing salt to allow for salt in mixture.

title: fudge squares
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour, butter and condensed milk. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, except marshmallows; mix well. Stir in marshmallows.
Spread in buttered pan, 12 x 8-inch.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 40 squares.

title: fried oysters
directions: Combine sour cream, eggs, onion salt and paprika.
Mix until blended, set aside.
Heat Crisco to 365° in deep pan.
Coat oysters with crumbs, dip into sour cream mixture; drain well.
Using a small amount of mashed potatoes, then adding more, coat oysters with mashed potato.
Fry oysters several at a time for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Serve warm with lemon wedges.

title: strawberry preserves(recipe of 1917)
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar and 1/3 cup of water; add 1 cup of strawberries and boil.
Add 1 cup of sugar and 1 cup of strawberries and boil.
Add another cup of strawberries and 1/3 cup sugar.
Boil for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand in glass bowl for 24 hours.
Skim and stir occasionally.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: raspberry swirl dessert
directions: Combine coconut and margarine. Press firmly on bottom and up side of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: crab delight dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 2 hours or make a day ahead.
Serve with chips, crackers or raw vegetables.

title: pea pulao(pakistan)
directions: Wash rice and let it soak for 15 minutes.
Saute onions until golden brown.
Add cloves, cardamom, black pepper and peas.
Drain the rice and add it to the pot of onions and spices.
Measure 3 1/2 cups of water and add to the rice mixture; add the salt.
Cook over medium heat until water has evaporated.
Cover with lid and turn to lowest temperature possible and let the rice sit for 5 minutes, then turn the heat off.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Bring to boil in microwave.
Microwave on High 2 minutes after boiling.
